1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,741
♪♪

2
00:00:08,809 --> 00:00:10,110
WHOOSH!

3
00:00:16,283 --> 00:00:19,386
♪ [melodic flute
and sustained strings] ♪

4
00:00:19,453 --> 00:00:37,971
♪  ♪

5
00:00:38,038 --> 00:00:40,440
[heavy thud of hooves
mixed with music]

6
00:00:40,507 --> 00:00:54,721
♪  ♪

7
00:00:54,788 --> 00:00:57,391
[whistles and applause
in the distance]

8
00:00:57,457 --> 00:01:00,627
♪ [strings and horns] ♪

9
00:01:00,694 --> 00:01:09,469
♪  ♪

10
00:01:09,536 --> 00:01:12,773
♪ [music swells majestically] ♪

11
00:01:12,839 --> 00:01:23,083
♪  ♪

12
00:01:23,150 --> 00:01:25,786
[bull bellowing
and snorting]

13
00:01:25,852 --> 00:01:40,334
♪  ♪

14
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:42,836
[many people applauding]

15
00:01:42,903 --> 00:01:46,740
♪  ♪

16
00:01:46,807 --> 00:01:48,175
[snoring]

17
00:01:48,241 --> 00:01:50,277
(Honeycut)
HEY SMOKEY, YOU IN THERE?

18
00:01:50,344 --> 00:01:51,979
HEY!

19
00:01:52,045 --> 00:01:53,413
UHG!

20
00:01:54,448 --> 00:01:56,216
AHH! CLOSE THE DOOR.

21
00:01:56,283 --> 00:01:58,385
OH MAN, LOOK AT YOU.

22
00:01:58,452 --> 00:02:00,420
YOU CAN'T
EVEN STAND UP.

23
00:02:00,487 --> 00:02:02,289
HOW ARE YOU
GONNA STAND ON. . .

24
00:02:02,356 --> 00:02:04,291
AH, I CAN'T BELIEVE THIS!

25
00:02:05,492 --> 00:02:06,760
[splat]

26
00:02:06,827 --> 00:02:09,029
OOO. . .OH!

27
00:02:09,096 --> 00:02:11,999
[crowd of people chattering
in the distance]

28
00:02:12,065 --> 00:02:13,433
C'MON!

29
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:14,768
ALL RIGHT!!!

30
00:02:14,835 --> 00:02:16,303
[crowd noise gets louder]

31
00:02:16,370 --> 00:02:18,405
(male announcer)
IF YOU'RE READY TO RODEO,

32
00:02:18,472 --> 00:02:19,973
WE'RE READY FOR YOU!

33
00:02:20,040 --> 00:02:22,042
(Honeycut) HERE, FINISH THIS.

34
00:02:22,109 --> 00:02:24,011
(announcer) IT'S RODEO TIME

35
00:02:24,077 --> 00:02:27,314
AS WE WELCOME YOU
TO THE BULL RIDE. . .

36
00:02:27,381 --> 00:02:30,283
[din of crowd talking]

37
00:02:30,350 --> 00:02:31,785
ARE YOU OKAY?

38
00:02:31,852 --> 00:02:33,153
YEAH,
I'M ALL RIGHT.

39
00:02:33,220 --> 00:02:35,656
YOU DON'T
LOOK ALL RIGHT.

40
00:02:38,058 --> 00:02:39,659
[loud exhale]

41
00:02:39,726 --> 00:02:41,528
(man)
GO GET 'EM COWBOY.

42
00:02:41,595 --> 00:02:43,363
THANKS.

43
00:02:43,430 --> 00:02:46,433
♪ [mandolin playing] ♪

44
00:02:46,500 --> 00:02:49,102
[crowd noise]

45
00:02:49,169 --> 00:02:50,604
SUCK IT UP MAN.

46
00:02:50,670 --> 00:02:51,671
I'M ALL RIGHT.

47
00:02:51,738 --> 00:02:53,073
SMOKEY BANKS?

48
00:02:53,140 --> 00:02:55,208
HEY, I'LL WORK ON
THEM FOR LATER.

49
00:02:57,144 --> 00:02:59,246
HEY GIRLS,
HOW YOU DOIN'?

50
00:02:59,312 --> 00:03:02,883
(announcer) TOP OF THE FIELD,
WORLD CHAMPION. . .

51
00:03:02,949 --> 00:03:04,818
GO GET 'EM COWBOY.

52
00:03:04,885 --> 00:03:06,520
(announcer)
FROM ARIZONA. . .

53
00:03:06,586 --> 00:03:09,256
HERE WE GO
WITH SMOKEY BANKS

54
00:03:09,322 --> 00:03:11,892
ON FEAR NO EVIL!

55
00:03:11,958 --> 00:03:14,661
IT'S 1,440 POUNDS
OF UNTRAINED. . .

56
00:03:14,728 --> 00:03:16,329
(Danny)
RIDE!!

57
00:03:16,396 --> 00:03:18,098
C'MON SMOKEY!!

58
00:03:18,165 --> 00:03:20,434
C'MON, RIDE HIM SMOKEY!

59
00:03:20,500 --> 00:03:21,968
(announcer)
HANG ON SMOKEY!

60
00:03:22,035 --> 00:03:24,337
LOOK AT HIM BUCK,

61
00:03:24,404 --> 00:03:27,541
AND SMOKEY IS DOWN
ON THE GROUND.

62
00:03:27,607 --> 00:03:30,277
[laughing]

63
00:03:30,343 --> 00:03:32,479
SMOKEY
GOT SMOKED!

64
00:03:32,546 --> 00:03:33,713
YEAH!

65
00:03:33,780 --> 00:03:35,449
IS THAT THE
BIG SMOKE-MAN?

66
00:03:35,515 --> 00:03:37,084
THAT YOUR HERO
OUT THERE?

67
00:03:38,552 --> 00:03:40,053
LET'S HEAD 'EM UP.

68
00:03:42,089 --> 00:03:43,557
YOU OKAY?

69
00:03:43,623 --> 00:03:46,660
YEAH--I JUST NEED
TO USE THE BATHROOM.

70
00:03:46,726 --> 00:03:49,429
WHY DON'T YOU
TAKE THE BOYS AND
HEAD BACK.

71
00:03:49,496 --> 00:03:52,065
ALL RIGHT. . .
C'MON BOYS.

72
00:03:52,132 --> 00:03:54,134
I'LL WAIT FOR YOU
IN THE TRUCK.

73
00:03:54,201 --> 00:03:57,971
♪  ♪

74
00:03:58,038 --> 00:03:59,973
[groaning]

75
00:03:59,973 --> 00:04:02,409
(announcer)
WELL COWBOY,
BETTER LUCK TO YOU.

76
00:04:02,476 --> 00:04:04,744
BACK TO
THE PRACTICE FIELD. . .

77
00:04:04,811 --> 00:04:09,082
BACK TO LAKE HAVASU CITY
WHERE THE DOGS DON'T BITE.

78
00:04:09,149 --> 00:04:11,718
WELL GOOD AFTERNOON,
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,

79
00:04:11,785 --> 00:04:14,087
THANKS FOR COMIN'
TO THE RODEO.

80
00:04:14,154 --> 00:04:17,290
GOD BLESS AND
HAPPY TRAILS TO YOU!

81
00:04:17,357 --> 00:04:28,969
♪  ♪

82
00:04:29,035 --> 00:04:30,504
[bull bellows]

83
00:04:30,570 --> 00:04:40,247
♪  ♪

84
00:04:40,313 --> 00:04:43,316
[snorting]

85
00:04:43,383 --> 00:04:46,386
♪  ♪

86
00:04:46,453 --> 00:04:55,328
[crowd noise]

87
00:04:55,395 --> 00:04:58,698
SMOKEY. . .I'D LIKE YOU
TO MEET NINA AND MARGO.

88
00:04:59,599 --> 00:05:01,268
LADIES. . .

89
00:05:01,334 --> 00:05:03,136
THEY'RE TWINS.

90
00:05:10,677 --> 00:05:13,013
[someone throwing up]

91
00:05:15,482 --> 00:05:17,384
UGH. . .[spits]

92
00:05:17,450 --> 00:05:23,089
[water running]

93
00:05:23,156 --> 00:05:25,592
[footsteps]

94
00:05:41,041 --> 00:05:43,410
[knocking]

95
00:05:43,476 --> 00:05:45,011
[gasping]

96
00:05:48,448 --> 00:05:50,083
[knocking]

97
00:05:50,150 --> 00:05:51,518
[loud gasping]

98
00:05:51,585 --> 00:05:53,453
I TOLD YOU I'D
PAY YOU BACK!

99
00:05:53,520 --> 00:05:55,322
I JUST NEED A LITTLE TIME.

100
00:05:55,388 --> 00:05:57,757
I GAVE YOU
ENOUGH TIME.

101
00:05:57,824 --> 00:05:59,159
AHH!!. . .[thud]

102
00:05:59,960 --> 00:06:01,828
[clatter]. . .OOOF!

103
00:06:02,562 --> 00:06:06,499
[wincing]

104
00:06:06,566 --> 00:06:07,667
YOU KNOW. . .

105
00:06:07,734 --> 00:06:10,070
I EVEN TOOK YOUR
STUPID BET ON THE VIKINGS.

106
00:06:10,136 --> 00:06:13,440
LOOK. . .THERE'S ANOTHER
RODEO IN A FEW WEEKS.

107
00:06:13,506 --> 00:06:15,775
I'LL WIN IT AND I'LL
PAY YOU BACK WITH INTEREST.

108
00:06:15,842 --> 00:06:17,177
I SWEAR!!

109
00:06:17,244 --> 00:06:19,512
AAAAHHHH!!. . .[thud]

110
00:06:21,481 --> 00:06:24,718
THE MONEY. . .
BY NEXT WEEK. . .

111
00:06:24,784 --> 00:06:27,020
OR. . .

112
00:06:27,087 --> 00:06:28,622
[loud gasping]

113
00:06:28,688 --> 00:06:31,925
[cracking sounds]

114
00:06:31,992 --> 00:06:35,095
SO. . .
WE HAVE AN UNDERSTANDING.

115
00:06:35,161 --> 00:06:37,464
YEAH.

116
00:06:41,134 --> 00:06:44,537
[wincing]

117
00:06:49,943 --> 00:06:59,753
[country guitar band
starts playing]

118
00:06:59,819 --> 00:07:03,323
(man singing)
♪ I'LL NEVER UNDERSTAND ♪

119
00:07:03,390 --> 00:07:06,593
♪ WHAT GETS
INTO A MAN ♪

120
00:07:06,660 --> 00:07:08,695
[Bang!
Bang!!]

121
00:07:08,762 --> 00:07:10,030
[Bang! Bang!]

122
00:07:10,096 --> 00:07:12,399
EVERYTHING OKAY
MR. BANKS?

123
00:07:12,465 --> 00:07:14,768
LEAVE ME ALONE,
WILL YA?

124
00:07:14,834 --> 00:07:17,570
THOSE MEN IN
THE BATHROOM. . .

125
00:07:17,637 --> 00:07:20,106
WE SHOULD CALL THE
POLICE AND TELL THEM.

126
00:07:20,173 --> 00:07:22,208
LISTEN KID. . .

127
00:07:22,275 --> 00:07:25,278
WHAT YOU SAW IN THERE
IS BETWEEN THEM AND ME.

128
00:07:25,345 --> 00:07:26,780
NOW GIT!

129
00:07:27,947 --> 00:07:30,317
BUT IF YOU CAN'T
PAY 'EM THEY'LL. . .

130
00:07:30,383 --> 00:07:32,452
ANYBODY EVER TEACH YOU
TO KEEP YOUR NOSE

131
00:07:32,519 --> 00:07:34,854
OUT OF OTHER PEOPLE'S BUSINESS?

132
00:07:40,193 --> 00:07:41,628
HERE.

133
00:07:41,695 --> 00:07:44,264
AIN'T TAKING NO MONEY
FROM NO KID.

134
00:07:48,768 --> 00:07:50,570
[rattling of coin
in slot]

135
00:07:52,739 --> 00:07:54,808
THANKS. . .
I OWE YA.

136
00:07:55,875 --> 00:07:57,777
[click,
click]

137
00:07:57,844 --> 00:07:58,912
[sighs]

138
00:08:00,547 --> 00:08:03,750
YOUR DADDY DOESN'T WORK FOR THE
PEPSI-COLA COMPANY DOES HE?

139
00:08:05,018 --> 00:08:06,553
NO.
GOOD.

140
00:08:06,619 --> 00:08:07,987
[smash]

141
00:08:08,054 --> 00:08:09,089
[rattling]

142
00:08:12,359 --> 00:08:14,260
LESSON IN
LIFE PARTNER. . .

143
00:08:14,327 --> 00:08:16,696
SOMETIMES YOU JUST GOTTA
WAIL ON IT AWHILE.

144
00:08:16,763 --> 00:08:19,065
(man)
SMOKEY!

145
00:08:19,132 --> 00:08:20,533
SMOKEY. . .

146
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:22,469
THE BANK GOT
YOUR TRAILER, MAN.

147
00:08:22,535 --> 00:08:23,770
WHAT!

148
00:08:23,837 --> 00:08:25,338
HEY, WAIT A SECOND!

149
00:08:25,405 --> 00:08:27,040
HEY!!

150
00:08:39,819 --> 00:08:42,055
[roar of engine]

151
00:08:43,656 --> 00:08:48,161
(woman singing
on truck radio]
♪ I COOKED YOUR DINNER ♪

152
00:08:48,228 --> 00:08:51,131
♪ I MADE YOUR BED ♪

153
00:08:53,600 --> 00:08:55,535
COME ON.

154
00:08:55,602 --> 00:08:57,871
(Billy Graham)
YOU'RE ALWAYS SEARCHING FOR
SOMETHING

155
00:08:57,937 --> 00:08:59,606
WHOA!!
AND YOU NEVER FIND IT.

156
00:08:59,672 --> 00:09:01,274
YOU CAN'T FIND IT IN SUCCESS,

157
00:09:01,341 --> 00:09:02,609
YOU CAN'T FIND IT IN SEX,

158
00:09:02,675 --> 00:09:04,210
YOU CAN'T FIND IT IN DRINK.

159
00:09:04,277 --> 00:09:06,246
YOU SAY, WELL,
WHAT DO I HAVE TO DO?

160
00:09:06,312 --> 00:09:08,214
CHANGE
THE STATION?

161
00:09:08,281 --> 00:09:10,150
(Billy Graham)
GOD LOVES YOU!

162
00:09:10,216 --> 00:09:12,252
CAN YOU IMAGINE THAT?

163
00:09:12,318 --> 00:09:14,087
WITH ALL YOUR FAILURES.

164
00:09:14,154 --> 00:09:16,256
YEAH, WELL THE
BANK HELPED.

165
00:09:16,322 --> 00:09:18,691
TO REPENT MEANS
TO TURN AROUND.

166
00:09:18,758 --> 00:09:21,194
YOU SEE, JESUS CHRIST

167
00:09:21,261 --> 00:09:23,196
THAT'S IT!
DIED ON THE
CROSS FOR YOU.

168
00:09:23,263 --> 00:09:24,664
[smack]
[radio cuts out]

169
00:09:24,731 --> 00:09:27,233
[loud roar
of engine acceleration]

170
00:09:27,300 --> 00:09:28,935
[horn honks]

171
00:09:29,002 --> 00:09:31,704
[loud steady blast of horn]

172
00:09:33,640 --> 00:09:34,908
PULL OVER!

173
00:09:34,974 --> 00:09:36,209
WHAT?

174
00:09:36,276 --> 00:09:37,777
PULL OVER!

175
00:09:38,578 --> 00:09:40,547
[screeching of tires]

176
00:09:43,450 --> 00:09:44,751
BACK OFF, BACK OFF!

177
00:09:44,818 --> 00:09:46,319
I ALREADY RADIOED
THE POLICE.

178
00:09:46,386 --> 00:09:47,687
I GOT NO BEEF
WITH YOU.

179
00:09:47,754 --> 00:09:48,955
I WANT
MY TRAILER BACK.

180
00:09:49,022 --> 00:09:50,423
EVERYTHING I OWN
IS IN THERE.

181
00:09:50,490 --> 00:09:51,958
SORRY PAL,
I CAN'T.

182
00:09:52,025 --> 00:09:53,393
HEY, WAIT
A MINUTE.

183
00:09:53,460 --> 00:09:54,961
AREN'T YOU
SMOKEY BANKS?

184
00:09:55,028 --> 00:09:56,729
YOU ARE, YOU'RE
SMOKEY BANKS!

185
00:09:56,796 --> 00:09:58,298
PLEASED TO
MEET YOU.
GOOD TO SEE YA.

186
00:09:58,364 --> 00:09:59,966
NOW CAN I HAVE
MY TAILER BACK?

187
00:10:00,033 --> 00:10:01,768
I CAN'T DO THAT.

188
00:10:01,835 --> 00:10:02,836
[thwack!]

189
00:10:02,902 --> 00:10:04,304
[thud]
OOF!

190
00:10:04,370 --> 00:10:05,805
(Hank)
HEY, HEY, HEY!

191
00:10:05,872 --> 00:10:08,675
OKAY LADIES, COME ON. . .

192
00:10:08,741 --> 00:10:10,677
IT'S LINE-UP TIME.

193
00:10:14,914 --> 00:10:16,916
UGH!

194
00:10:16,983 --> 00:10:18,351
OOOH!

195
00:10:19,052 --> 00:10:20,787
AAAHH!

196
00:10:20,854 --> 00:10:22,255
[loud clunk]

197
00:10:22,322 --> 00:10:27,527
[whirring of electric motor]

198
00:10:27,594 --> 00:10:28,595
[clunk]

199
00:10:33,032 --> 00:10:34,434
THAT'S HIM.

200
00:10:35,735 --> 00:10:37,770
HI MR. BANKS.

201
00:10:37,837 --> 00:10:40,773
HEY, WHAT DO
YOU MEAN, "THAT'S HIM?"

202
00:10:40,840 --> 00:10:42,175
[rumble of car engine]

203
00:10:42,242 --> 00:10:44,978
WHAT'S YOU'RE
DEFINITION OF BOTTOM?

204
00:10:45,044 --> 00:10:46,379
BOY?

205
00:10:54,821 --> 00:10:56,356
THIS.

206
00:10:58,892 --> 00:11:00,827
THAT'S ACTUALLY
A GOOD ANSWER.

207
00:11:02,295 --> 00:11:04,898
90 DAYS,
THAT'S A LONG TIME.

208
00:11:06,032 --> 00:11:08,268
WHAT IF I
DON'T LIKE THIS?

209
00:11:08,935 --> 00:11:10,803
YOU WILL. . .

210
00:11:10,870 --> 00:11:12,472
BEATS JAIL!

211
00:11:21,114 --> 00:11:24,784
(Hank)
THEY'VE BEEN ASKIN' AROUND FOR
A COWBOY THE PAST FEW MONTHS.

212
00:11:24,851 --> 00:11:27,754
ALL THE OTHER GUYS I ASKED
HAD SERIOUS COMMITMENTS.

213
00:11:27,820 --> 00:11:30,924
YOU. . .YOU HAVE SOME
TIME ON YOUR HANDS,

214
00:11:30,990 --> 00:11:32,759
YOU'LL DO.

215
00:11:32,825 --> 00:11:36,696
BESIDES IT WAS
THEIR TRUCK YOU STOLE.

216
00:11:39,899 --> 00:11:41,100
[click]

217
00:11:44,103 --> 00:11:46,039
SO WE GOT A LIVE ONE.

218
00:11:47,440 --> 00:11:49,809
YEAH. SMOKEY BANKS. . .

219
00:11:49,876 --> 00:11:52,445
MIKE STILLWELL,
RANCH DIRECTOR.

220
00:11:52,512 --> 00:11:54,480
SORRY ABOUT YOUR TRUCK.

221
00:11:54,547 --> 00:11:57,350
ACCEPTED. WELCOME TO
SAGUARO BOYS RANCH.

222
00:11:57,417 --> 00:11:59,219
GLAD WE COULD
WORK US A DEAL.

223
00:11:59,285 --> 00:12:01,120
LET'S SHOW YOU AROUND.

224
00:12:01,187 --> 00:12:03,856
THE GUYS HERE WILL
WARM UP TO YA.

225
00:12:05,558 --> 00:12:07,660
HEY,
SMOKEY BANKS.

226
00:12:07,727 --> 00:12:09,796
HEY GUYS,
SMOKEY'S HERE.

227
00:12:09,862 --> 00:12:11,431
EXCEPT OF
COURSE, DANNY.

228
00:12:12,465 --> 00:12:14,734
HI, MR. BANKS.
PUT 'ER THERE.

229
00:12:14,801 --> 00:12:17,537
DANNY'S RESPONSIBLE
FOR YOU BEIN' HERE.

230
00:12:18,771 --> 00:12:20,406
YA I KNOW.

231
00:12:20,473 --> 00:12:23,076
HEY C'MON, WE'LL HAVE
LOTS OF FUN.

232
00:12:23,142 --> 00:12:24,477
HEY BIG GUY,

233
00:12:24,544 --> 00:12:26,079
WHY DON'T YOU
CATCH YOUR BREATH.

234
00:12:26,145 --> 00:12:27,547
GET A DRINK OF WATER.

235
00:12:27,614 --> 00:12:29,582
YOU'LL HAVE PLENTY OF TIME TO
SPEND WITH MR. BANKS.

236
00:12:29,649 --> 00:12:31,084
ALL RIGHT.

237
00:12:32,885 --> 00:12:35,188
WE SET UP 10 YEARS AGO

238
00:12:35,254 --> 00:12:37,624
TO TAKE IN BOYS
FROM TROUBLED SITUATIONS,

239
00:12:37,690 --> 00:12:39,559
WHETHER AT HOME OR WITH THE LAW.

240
00:12:44,230 --> 00:12:46,532
ONCE THEY GET HERE, WE
DON'T ASK 'EM ABOUT THE PAST.

241
00:12:46,599 --> 00:12:48,501
THEY TEND TO BUILD THAT UP.

242
00:12:48,568 --> 00:12:49,969
AND ME?

243
00:12:50,036 --> 00:12:51,270
THAT BOY
YOU JUST MET?

244
00:12:51,337 --> 00:12:52,405
YA.

245
00:12:52,472 --> 00:12:53,773
YOU'RE IN CHARGE
OF HIM

246
00:12:53,840 --> 00:12:55,108
WHILE YOU'RE HERE.

247
00:12:55,174 --> 00:12:56,476
WHY ME?

248
00:12:56,542 --> 00:12:57,810
DANNY'S 14 NOW.

249
00:12:57,877 --> 00:12:58,978
SEVERAL YEARS AGO,

250
00:12:59,045 --> 00:13:00,947
HIS PARENTS WERE BOTH KILLED BY
A DRUNK DRIVER.

251
00:13:01,014 --> 00:13:02,682
NOW WAIT
A DOGGONE MINUTE.

252
00:13:02,749 --> 00:13:05,818
THERE'S NO WAY THIS
IS GONNA WORK OUT,

253
00:13:05,885 --> 00:13:07,654
YOU KNOW THAT?

254
00:13:07,720 --> 00:13:09,989
NO WAY AT ALL.

255
00:13:10,056 --> 00:13:13,292
SEEMS TO ME THAT MIKE HERE
IS BEING OVERLY GENEROUS

256
00:13:13,359 --> 00:13:14,727
AGREEING TO DROP CHARGES

257
00:13:14,794 --> 00:13:17,096
IF YOU DO THESE PEOPLE
THIS FAVOR.

258
00:13:17,163 --> 00:13:19,932
YOU CALL BEING HERE
AGAINST MY WILL A
FAVOR?

259
00:13:19,999 --> 00:13:21,901
HEY, IT'S YOUR CHOICE.

260
00:13:21,968 --> 00:13:24,237
STAY HERE,
OR FOLLOW ME TO MY CAR

261
00:13:24,303 --> 00:13:26,239
WHERE I'LL TAKE YOU
STRAIGHT TO JAIL.

262
00:13:29,275 --> 00:13:32,211
♪ [strings & flute] ♪

263
00:13:32,278 --> 00:13:49,529
♪  ♪

264
00:13:49,595 --> 00:13:51,731
I MAKE YOUR BED
THE FIRST TIME,

265
00:13:51,798 --> 00:13:54,167
CLEAN SHEETS
AND TOWELS ONCE A WEEK.

266
00:13:54,233 --> 00:13:56,135
THE SHOWER IS THERE,
BREAKFAST IS AT 6,

267
00:13:56,202 --> 00:13:58,204
I'M ELLEN, HELLO, WELCOME.

268
00:13:58,271 --> 00:13:59,772
I'VE GOT A HORSE WAITING.

269
00:13:59,839 --> 00:14:01,874
YUP, THAT'S
MY WIFE.

270
00:14:10,416 --> 00:14:12,618
SO THIS KID YOU
WERE TELLING ME ABOUT,

271
00:14:12,685 --> 00:14:14,821
WHAT DO YOU WANT ME
TO DO WITH HIM?

272
00:14:14,887 --> 00:14:16,856
TEACH HIM HOW
TO RIDE BULL.

273
00:14:16,923 --> 00:14:18,825
SAY AGAIN?

274
00:14:18,891 --> 00:14:20,660
WORK WITH HIM.

275
00:14:22,095 --> 00:14:24,731
HOW'S ABOUT WE PUT SOMETHIN' ON
THE TABLE FOR ME IN RETURN?

276
00:14:24,797 --> 00:14:27,567
THERE'S A RODEO
IN A FEW WEEKS.

277
00:14:27,633 --> 00:14:29,569
I WANNA COMPETE.

278
00:14:29,635 --> 00:14:31,337
OKAY?

279
00:14:32,105 --> 00:14:33,973
NO PROMISES.

280
00:14:34,040 --> 00:14:35,942
JUST DO YOUR JOB.

281
00:14:41,814 --> 00:14:43,616
[loud sigh]

282
00:14:47,086 --> 00:14:51,924
[boards creaking]

283
00:14:51,991 --> 00:14:54,994
[crickets chirping]

284
00:14:55,061 --> 00:14:58,030
HEY. . .HOW'S MY
LITTLE HEIFER?

285
00:15:00,233 --> 00:15:02,301
GOOD.

286
00:15:03,269 --> 00:15:05,271
YOU FEEL LIKE PARTYIN'?

287
00:15:05,338 --> 00:15:07,540
(Dennis)
WOW, CHECK IT OUT.

288
00:15:07,607 --> 00:15:08,808
(George)
GIRLS.

289
00:15:08,875 --> 00:15:10,009
NO KIDDING, GIRLS--

290
00:15:10,076 --> 00:15:11,677
I'LL BET HE HAS
AT LEAST 20 GIRLFRIENDS.

291
00:15:11,744 --> 00:15:13,479
THESE ARE JUST
HIS SWIMMING
GIRLFRIENDS.

292
00:15:13,546 --> 00:15:14,847
UNDOUBTEDLY.

293
00:15:14,914 --> 00:15:16,816
I DIDN'T
KNOW GIRLS
HAD SO MUCH SKIN.

294
00:15:16,916 --> 00:15:18,985
HEY, LET'S GET A
CLOSER LOOK.

295
00:15:19,051 --> 00:15:20,520
WAIT, WAIT,
NOT A GOOD IDEA.

296
00:15:20,586 --> 00:15:22,288
YOU KNOW HE'S KILLED
ABOUT 4 GUYS.

297
00:15:22,355 --> 00:15:23,890
OH YEAH.

298
00:15:25,391 --> 00:15:26,225
BINOCULARS!

299
00:15:26,292 --> 00:15:26,993
GREAT IDEA.

300
00:15:27,059 --> 00:15:27,827
GO GET 'EM.

301
00:15:27,894 --> 00:15:29,428
C'MON GO GET 'EM,
HURRY UP!

302
00:15:29,495 --> 00:15:31,631
OKAY. DON'T' LET ANYTHING
COOL HAPPEN WHILE I'M GONE.

303
00:15:34,233 --> 00:15:36,302
THE KEY TO CARVING LEATHER WELL

304
00:15:36,369 --> 00:15:38,538
IS KNOWING HOW DEEP TO GO.

305
00:15:38,604 --> 00:15:40,373
ONE MISTAKE IN THE CUT

306
00:15:40,439 --> 00:15:42,275
OR ANY VARIATION
FROM THE PATTERN,

307
00:15:42,341 --> 00:15:44,377
THEN IT'S HARD TO RECOVER.

308
00:15:45,845 --> 00:15:47,346
WHAT'S GOING
ON DENNIS?

309
00:15:47,413 --> 00:15:50,416
OH, HI MRS. STILLWELL. HI MIKE.

310
00:15:50,483 --> 00:15:52,952
(sounds nervous) I WAS JUST
PASSING THROUGH HERE.

311
00:15:53,019 --> 00:15:56,088
I. . .I'M KINDA TIRED SO I--

312
00:15:56,155 --> 00:16:00,226
I'M GONNA TAKE A WALK BEFORE I
GO TO--GO TO BED.

313
00:16:00,293 --> 00:16:01,994
[fire crackling]

314
00:16:02,061 --> 00:16:03,963
[crickets chirping]

315
00:16:04,030 --> 00:16:05,097
[owl hooting]

316
00:16:05,164 --> 00:16:06,098
[coyote howling]

317
00:16:06,165 --> 00:16:07,500
GIVE ME
THE BINOCULARS.

318
00:16:07,567 --> 00:16:09,068
NO. GIVE 'EM
TO ME.

319
00:16:09,135 --> 00:16:10,436
GIVE 'EM TO ME.

320
00:16:10,503 --> 00:16:13,606
BOYS. . .BACK TO
THE RANCH

321
00:16:13,673 --> 00:16:15,107
NOW!!

322
00:16:15,174 --> 00:16:19,212
(all) HE MADE ME DO IT!
HE PUSHED ME!!
I DIDN'T WANT TO!

323
00:16:19,278 --> 00:16:22,248
[dripping of water]

324
00:16:22,315 --> 00:16:25,151
(Mike)
ALCOHOL ON RANCH GROUNDS,

325
00:16:25,218 --> 00:16:26,853
BREAKING CURFEW,

326
00:16:26,919 --> 00:16:29,322
UNREGISTERED GUEST, WHAT ELSE?

327
00:16:29,388 --> 00:16:32,625
I DON'T KNOW WHAT KIND OF
LIFESTYLE YOU'RE ACCUSTOMED TO,

328
00:16:32,692 --> 00:16:37,263
BUT AROUND HERE EVERYONE LIVES
BY THE SAME RULES.

329
00:16:39,332 --> 00:16:41,834
SO, NO SWIMMING?

330
00:16:41,901 --> 00:16:44,036
THIS ISN'T A JOKE.

331
00:16:44,103 --> 00:16:46,138
I CANNOT AND WILL NOT

332
00:16:46,205 --> 00:16:47,907
TOLERATE ANY BEHAVIOR HERE

333
00:16:47,974 --> 00:16:50,376
THAT JEOPARDIZES
ANYONE'S WELL-BEING.

334
00:16:50,443 --> 00:16:53,946
JEOPARDIZES? MY FRIENDS
AND I KNOW HOW TO SWIM.

335
00:16:54,013 --> 00:16:56,782
EVERYTHING YOU DO FOR
THE NEXT 3 MONTHS

336
00:16:56,849 --> 00:16:59,118
WILL AFFECT SOMEONE ELSE.

337
00:16:59,185 --> 00:17:02,088
YOU DO ANYTHING,
THEY WILL IMITATE YOU.

338
00:17:02,154 --> 00:17:04,490
I DON'T KNOW ANYTHING ABOUT
ANYBODY IMITATIN' ME.

339
00:17:04,557 --> 00:17:06,225
I WAS JUST TRYIN' TO RELAX!

340
00:17:06,292 --> 00:17:08,628
WE RELAX ON SUNDAY.

341
00:17:08,694 --> 00:17:11,230
NOW IF YOU WANT TO STAY HERE,

342
00:17:11,297 --> 00:17:13,666
YOU GOTTA PLAY BY OUR RULES.

343
00:17:13,733 --> 00:17:16,102
WE HAVE RANK HERE.

344
00:17:16,168 --> 00:17:18,404
FROM THIS MOMENT FORTH SMOKEY,

345
00:17:18,471 --> 00:17:22,308
YOU ARE A RANCH HAND,
THE LOWEST RANK.

346
00:17:22,375 --> 00:17:24,577
YOU MAY NOT LEAVE THE GROUNDS

347
00:17:24,644 --> 00:17:29,615
UNLESS A GUY OF SCOUT
OR HIGHER RANK IS WITH YOU.

348
00:17:29,682 --> 00:17:31,651
YOU TELLIN' ME THAT I NEED
PERMISSION

349
00:17:31,717 --> 00:17:34,120
FROM ONE OF THESE LITTLE RUNTS
TO CROSS THE STREET?

350
00:17:34,186 --> 00:17:35,655
THAT'S RIGHT.

351
00:17:35,721 --> 00:17:37,356
NOW THAT'S A JOKE!

352
00:17:37,423 --> 00:17:39,158
PART OF YOUR TIME
HERE COULD BE

353
00:17:39,225 --> 00:17:42,128
TO GET YOU BACK
INTO THE REAL WORLD.

354
00:17:42,194 --> 00:17:43,429
WE COULD HELP.

355
00:17:43,496 --> 00:17:46,299
YOU LET ME COMPETE IN THAT RODEO
I WAS TELLIN' YOU ABOUT,

356
00:17:46,365 --> 00:17:48,134
AND I'LL SHOW
I STILL GOT THE STUFF.

357
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:50,536
A RANCH HAND DOES NOT
LEAVE THE GROUNDS

358
00:17:50,603 --> 00:17:53,773
UNLESS THE HIGHER RANKING GUYS
GIVE HIM THEIR PERMISSION,

359
00:17:53,839 --> 00:17:56,108
AND THAT INCLUDES RODEO.

360
00:17:56,175 --> 00:17:58,611
WE'LL SEE ABOUT THAT.

361
00:18:03,349 --> 00:18:06,786
AT LEAST IN JAIL THEY DON'T
EXPECT NOTHIN' OF YA.

362
00:18:06,852 --> 00:18:10,456
[loud footsteps]

363
00:18:10,523 --> 00:18:12,091
[loud sigh]

364
00:18:22,535 --> 00:18:24,870
[deep inhale]

365
00:18:24,937 --> 00:18:27,173
[deep exhale]

366
00:18:29,275 --> 00:18:30,476
OOH!

367
00:18:33,913 --> 00:18:36,515
(with disgust)
RANCH HAND.

368
00:18:36,582 --> 00:18:38,050
[sighs]

369
00:18:40,019 --> 00:18:42,221
PERMISSION TO RODEO.

370
00:18:44,590 --> 00:18:47,827
THE SNOT-NOSED LITTLE RUNTS!

371
00:18:57,703 --> 00:18:59,138
AAAAAAHHH!!!

372
00:18:59,205 --> 00:19:00,773
[squealing]

373
00:19:00,773 --> 00:19:01,540
[snort, snort]

374
00:19:01,607 --> 00:19:03,976
C'MON DANNY,
YOU CAN DO IT!

375
00:19:04,043 --> 00:19:05,244
ALL RIGHT!!

376
00:19:05,311 --> 00:19:07,713
(Dennis)
I RODE IT BEFORE.
YOU'RE GONNA BE FINE.

377
00:19:07,780 --> 00:19:09,448
YOU CAN DO IT, MAN.

378
00:19:11,484 --> 00:19:14,453
C'MON DANNY. GET ON.

379
00:19:14,520 --> 00:19:17,423
[Danny groaning slightly]

380
00:19:17,490 --> 00:19:20,159
[horse breathing forcefully]

381
00:19:20,226 --> 00:19:23,329
[Danny winces]

382
00:19:23,396 --> 00:19:24,830
[birds chirping]

383
00:19:24,897 --> 00:19:26,899
[horse breathing forcefully]

384
00:19:26,966 --> 00:19:28,167
[boys laughing]

385
00:19:28,234 --> 00:19:29,368
GREAT HORSE!

386
00:19:29,435 --> 00:19:30,736
HA, HA, HA, HA, HA.

387
00:19:30,803 --> 00:19:31,971
[birds chirping]

388
00:19:32,038 --> 00:19:33,439
HEY. . .GUYS,
THIS IS EASY.

389
00:19:33,506 --> 00:19:34,607
[swak]

390
00:19:34,673 --> 00:19:36,742
♪ [brisk orchestral music] ♪

391
00:19:36,809 --> 00:19:38,277
♪  ♪

392
00:19:38,344 --> 00:19:40,046
RIDE THAT
HORSE,
DANNY.

393
00:19:40,112 --> 00:19:43,115
AH. . .AH!

394
00:19:44,150 --> 00:19:45,418
YEAH!

395
00:19:45,484 --> 00:19:47,019
[horse whinnies]

396
00:19:47,086 --> 00:19:48,320
OKAY!

397
00:19:48,387 --> 00:19:50,289
[horse snorts and whinnies]

398
00:19:50,356 --> 00:19:51,657
♪  ♪

399
00:19:51,724 --> 00:19:53,192
[boys laughing]

400
00:19:53,259 --> 00:19:54,960
WHOA. . .WHOA!!

401
00:19:55,027 --> 00:19:56,829
[fast clompety-clomp
of hooves]

402
00:19:56,896 --> 00:19:58,831
(Danny) HELP!!
(Smokey) WHOA! HOLD ON TO HIM!

403
00:19:58,898 --> 00:20:02,868
♪  ♪

404
00:20:02,935 --> 00:20:04,203
MA'AM. . .
HYAAA!!

405
00:20:04,270 --> 00:20:08,174
♪  ♪

406
00:20:08,240 --> 00:20:09,675
MA'AM???

407
00:20:09,742 --> 00:20:11,610
♪  ♪

408
00:20:11,677 --> 00:20:14,013
C'MON,
GITUP--C'MON.

409
00:20:14,080 --> 00:20:18,751
♪  ♪

410
00:20:18,818 --> 00:20:20,119
C'MON
GIDDYUP!

411
00:20:20,186 --> 00:20:32,431
♪  ♪

412
00:20:32,498 --> 00:20:34,733
WHOA!!
HOLD HIM!

413
00:20:34,800 --> 00:20:36,102
♪  ♪

414
00:20:36,168 --> 00:20:37,570
[whinnies]

415
00:20:43,042 --> 00:20:44,643
OF ALL THE STUPID THINGS.

416
00:20:44,710 --> 00:20:46,278
WHAT WERE YOU THINKIN'?

417
00:20:46,345 --> 00:20:48,514
YOU COULD'VE
GOT YOURSELF KILLED. . .

418
00:20:48,581 --> 00:20:50,683
OH, IT'S YOU AGAIN.

419
00:20:50,750 --> 00:20:52,651
WELL NOW THAT I GOT
YOU HERE BY YOURSELF,

420
00:20:52,718 --> 00:20:54,220
I'D LIKE TO ASK
YOU SOMETHING.

421
00:20:54,286 --> 00:20:55,621
HOW COME YOU RATTED
ME OUT TO THE COPS?

422
00:20:55,688 --> 00:20:56,822
WELL FOR WHAT?

423
00:20:56,889 --> 00:20:58,557
FOR KICKIN'
THE SODA MACHINE.

424
00:20:58,624 --> 00:21:00,359
I DIDN'T TELL 'EM
ANYTHING ABOUT
THAT.

425
00:21:00,426 --> 00:21:03,629
WELL. . .THEN. . .
HOW DID I GET HERE?

426
00:21:03,696 --> 00:21:05,598
I PRAYED YOU HERE.

427
00:21:05,664 --> 00:21:06,966
YOU WHAT?

428
00:21:08,334 --> 00:21:10,236
I PRAYED YOU'D COME
HERE.

429
00:21:13,506 --> 00:21:17,777
SO YOU SAID A PRAYER, AND GOD
MADE ME STEAL YOUR TRUCK?

430
00:21:17,843 --> 00:21:21,213
NO, I THINK YOU DID
THAT PART ALL ON
YOUR OWN.

431
00:21:21,280 --> 00:21:25,317
YOU KNOW, THERE'S WAY TOO MUCH
PRAYING GOIN' ON AROUND HERE.

432
00:21:25,384 --> 00:21:28,254
[horse snorts]

433
00:21:30,389 --> 00:21:32,892
SO YOU WANT
TO RIDE A BULL?

434
00:21:32,958 --> 00:21:34,727
YUP. . .

435
00:21:34,793 --> 00:21:38,430
HEY, I'VE BEEN A FAN
OF YOURS FOREVER. . .

436
00:21:38,497 --> 00:21:42,234
'87, YOU BROKE EL GRANDE
IN SANTA FE.

437
00:21:42,301 --> 00:21:45,437
'89, AUGUSTA MONTANA,

438
00:21:45,504 --> 00:21:47,306
A FULL 8 SECONDS
ON THUNDER.

439
00:21:47,373 --> 00:21:49,241
I MEAN '90--
DIZZY DEAN!

440
00:21:49,308 --> 00:21:51,177
'87, YOU EVEN
BORN THEN?

441
00:21:56,282 --> 00:21:58,951
MY DAD WAS
YOUR BIGGEST FAN.

442
00:22:00,286 --> 00:22:02,388
WE'D GO TO THE RODEOS
AND WATCH THE COWBOYS--

443
00:22:02,454 --> 00:22:04,890
THEY'D RIDE GOOD,
BUT,

444
00:22:04,957 --> 00:22:07,793
YOU KNOW, HE'D ALWAYS SAY,
WAIT 'TIL SMOKEY RIDES,

445
00:22:07,860 --> 00:22:09,562
HE'LL BEAT 'EM ALL.

446
00:22:13,299 --> 00:22:15,768
MY DAD ALSO
TAUGHT ME TO PRAY.

447
00:22:15,835 --> 00:22:18,237
GUESS THAT'S WHERE
I PICKED IT UP.

448
00:22:18,304 --> 00:22:20,239
YEAH.

449
00:22:23,642 --> 00:22:26,812
I DIDN'T KNOW GOD
WAS IN THE BULL
RIDIN' BUSINESS.

450
00:22:26,879 --> 00:22:29,615
HE'S IN YOUR BUSINESS
IF YOU LET HIM.

451
00:22:29,682 --> 00:22:31,717
IS THAT A FACT.

452
00:22:31,784 --> 00:22:33,986
YUP.

453
00:22:34,053 --> 00:22:36,288
I PICKED UP THE
BIBLE ONCE,

454
00:22:36,355 --> 00:22:38,057
SAT DOWN,
OPENED IT UP.

455
00:22:38,123 --> 00:22:41,126
IT SAID, "THOU
SHALT NOT," SO I
DIDN'T.

456
00:22:41,193 --> 00:22:44,029
LISTEN DANNY,
THERE'S AH. . .

457
00:22:44,096 --> 00:22:46,632
SOMETHING I WANT TO
TALK TO YOU ABOUT.

458
00:22:46,699 --> 00:22:48,300
IT'S BEEN
ON MY MIND.

459
00:22:48,367 --> 00:22:51,637
YOU KEEP PRAYIN'
ALL YOU WANT.

460
00:22:51,704 --> 00:22:54,406
LET'S GET THIS
ONE THING STRAIGHT.

461
00:22:54,473 --> 00:22:57,343
I'M MOVIN' ON.

462
00:22:57,409 --> 00:23:01,380
I'M DOIN' MY TIME HERE,
AND THEN I'M MOVIN' ON.

463
00:23:01,447 --> 00:23:03,649
I'LL HELP YOU OUT CAUSE
I GOT NOTHIN' BETTER TO DO,

464
00:23:03,716 --> 00:23:06,085
THEN I'M GONE.

465
00:23:06,151 --> 00:23:08,020
ALL RIGHT?

466
00:23:09,755 --> 00:23:11,690
ALL RIGHT.

467
00:23:11,757 --> 00:23:19,932
♪   ♪

468
00:23:19,999 --> 00:23:22,635
SMOKEY. . .
HAVE A SEAT.

469
00:23:22,701 --> 00:23:24,904
EVERYONE KNOW SMOKEY BANKS?

470
00:23:24,970 --> 00:23:26,705
MY NIECE, LINNETTE.

471
00:23:26,772 --> 00:23:28,774
I BELIEVE I'VE
HAD THAT PLEASURE.

472
00:23:28,841 --> 00:23:40,119
[boys conversing]

473
00:23:40,185 --> 00:23:43,022
AH--DANNY'S A LITTLE
UNDER THE WEATHER TONIGHT.

474
00:23:46,292 --> 00:23:48,127
JUST--JUST HELP YOURSELF.

475
00:23:48,193 --> 00:23:49,295
THANK YOU.

476
00:23:49,361 --> 00:23:51,930
EVERYTHING GONNA WORK OUT
BETWEEN YOU TWO?

477
00:23:53,265 --> 00:23:55,234
WE HAVE
AN UNDERSTANDING.

478
00:23:55,301 --> 00:23:56,969
AH. . .OKAY.

479
00:23:58,137 --> 00:23:59,538
THANK YOU, MA'AM.

480
00:23:59,538 --> 00:24:01,307
HAVE SOME MILK, SMOKEY.

481
00:24:05,644 --> 00:24:12,084
[all conversing pleasantly]

482
00:24:14,787 --> 00:24:16,622
(Mike)
DEAR LORD,

483
00:24:16,689 --> 00:24:18,590
THANK YOU FOR THIS FOOD,

484
00:24:18,657 --> 00:24:20,726
AND EVERYTHING ELSE
YOU'VE PROVIDED TODAY.

485
00:24:20,793 --> 00:24:22,661
BLESS THOSE IN WANT,

486
00:24:22,728 --> 00:24:26,598
AND A SPECIAL THANK YOU
FOR DELIVERIN' SMOKEY TO US.

487
00:24:26,665 --> 00:24:29,802
IN JESUS NAME, AMEN.

488
00:24:29,868 --> 00:24:31,070
AMEN!
AMEN!

489
00:24:34,073 --> 00:24:37,409
[crickets chirping]

490
00:24:37,476 --> 00:24:39,178
[coyote yipping]

491
00:24:39,244 --> 00:24:41,213
♪ [harp and flute] ♪

492
00:24:41,280 --> 00:24:55,094
♪  ♪

493
00:24:55,160 --> 00:24:57,062
[deep exhale]

494
00:24:57,129 --> 00:25:19,518
♪  ♪

495
00:25:19,585 --> 00:25:20,552
[splat]

496
00:25:20,619 --> 00:25:22,187
(whispering)
Get the chairs--the chairs.

497
00:25:22,254 --> 00:25:23,288
The chairs.

498
00:25:23,355 --> 00:25:27,192
[owl hoots]

499
00:25:27,259 --> 00:25:29,194
(Steve) C'mon. . .C'mon!

500
00:25:29,261 --> 00:25:33,232
♪  ♪

501
00:25:33,298 --> 00:25:34,967
[squeaking]

502
00:25:37,603 --> 00:25:39,571
Come here. C'mon,
give it to me!

503
00:25:39,638 --> 00:25:42,441
♪ [orchestral music
becomes suspenseful] ♪

504
00:25:42,508 --> 00:25:48,046
♪  ♪

505
00:25:48,113 --> 00:25:50,883
All right, c'mon,
let's go! We got it!

506
00:25:50,949 --> 00:25:52,217
♪   ♪

507
00:25:52,284 --> 00:25:54,219
[clattering sounds]

508
00:25:56,388 --> 00:25:57,689
(all)
WHOO!-WHOO!-WHOO!-WHOO!

509
00:25:57,756 --> 00:26:00,192
WHOO!-WHOO!-WHOO!-WHOO!
WHOO!-WHOO!-WHOO!-WHOO!

510
00:26:00,259 --> 00:26:01,493
[whoosh!!]

511
00:26:01,560 --> 00:26:02,461
[thud]

512
00:26:02,528 --> 00:26:04,329
HA, HA, HA, HA, HA.

513
00:26:04,396 --> 00:26:06,398
HEY, I'M GONNA GET YOU,
YOU MORONS!

514
00:26:06,465 --> 00:26:08,133
COME ON OUT!

515
00:26:08,200 --> 00:26:10,803
I'M GONNA KILL YOU!
COME ON OUT!

516
00:26:10,869 --> 00:26:12,905
♪  ♪

517
00:26:12,971 --> 00:26:13,972
[click]

518
00:26:16,575 --> 00:26:18,444
HEY.

519
00:26:18,510 --> 00:26:22,714
[birds chirping & owl hooting]

520
00:26:22,781 --> 00:26:24,450
WHAT.

521
00:26:24,516 --> 00:26:27,052
HOW WAS YOUR
EVENIN' LAST NIGHT.

522
00:26:27,119 --> 00:26:29,087
WHY?

523
00:26:29,154 --> 00:26:31,590
YOU KNOW WHO DID
IT, DON'T YOU?

524
00:26:31,657 --> 00:26:33,592
I CAN GUESS.

525
00:26:33,659 --> 00:26:35,594
I GOT THE PERFECT
PLAN TO GET 'EM BACK.

526
00:26:35,661 --> 00:26:37,362
WAIT 'TILL YOU
HEAR THIS!

527
00:26:37,429 --> 00:26:39,064
I'M NOT GONNA
GET 'EM BACK.

528
00:26:39,131 --> 00:26:40,532
PARDON.

529
00:26:40,599 --> 00:26:41,800
I THOUGHT ABOUT IT,

530
00:26:41,867 --> 00:26:43,535
AND I DECIDED I'M
NOT GONNA DO ANYTHING.

531
00:26:43,602 --> 00:26:45,971
WELL THEY MADE A FOOL
OUT OF YOU SON.

532
00:26:46,038 --> 00:26:48,440
WELL LAST NIGHT
I WOULD'VE KILLED 'EM.

533
00:26:48,507 --> 00:26:50,642
JUST NOT TODAY.

534
00:26:50,709 --> 00:26:52,644
WELL WE CAN'T LET 'EM
GET AWAY WITH IT.

535
00:26:52,711 --> 00:26:54,112
I'M SORT OF
IN CHARGE OF YA.

536
00:26:54,179 --> 00:26:55,981
IF YOU'RE NOT GONNA
DO ANYTHING ABOUT IT,

537
00:26:56,048 --> 00:26:58,016
THEN I WILL.

538
00:26:58,884 --> 00:27:00,886
AT THE SODA MACHINE,

539
00:27:00,953 --> 00:27:03,555
YOU SAID SOMETIMES YOU
JUST HAVE TO WAIL ON IT AWHILE.

540
00:27:03,622 --> 00:27:07,392
WELL, SOMETIMES YOU JUST
HAVE TO LET IT GO.

541
00:27:08,861 --> 00:27:10,362
LISTEN. . .

542
00:27:10,429 --> 00:27:12,764
YOU BETTER PLAN ON LIVIN'
THE REST OF YOUR LIFE

543
00:27:12,831 --> 00:27:15,100
AT THIS STUPID RANCH 'CAUSE
YOU'RE NEVER GONNA MAKE IT

544
00:27:15,167 --> 00:27:17,369
OUT THERE IN
THE REAL WORLD.

545
00:27:20,072 --> 00:27:21,440
[thwak
thwak]

546
00:27:28,580 --> 00:27:30,482
[whinnies]

547
00:27:30,549 --> 00:27:32,818
(Mike)
I THOUGHT THE BEST WAY
TO GET YOU ALL ACQUAINTED

548
00:27:32,885 --> 00:27:35,587
IS FOR YOU TO TAKE SMOKEY
ON A TRAIL RIDE.

549
00:27:35,654 --> 00:27:37,422
BE BACK FOR SUPPER.

550
00:27:37,489 --> 00:27:39,224
ALL RIGHT. . .OKAY.

551
00:27:39,291 --> 00:27:41,126
WHERE'S THE KID?

552
00:27:41,193 --> 00:27:43,462
DANNY? SAID HE HAD
TO CLEAN UP HIS ROOM.

553
00:27:43,529 --> 00:27:46,632
[neighs & whinnies]

554
00:27:46,698 --> 00:27:49,968
YOU GUYS LOOK
HALF-WAY DECENT.

555
00:27:50,035 --> 00:27:53,572
LINNETTE TAUGHT US. SHE'S
IN CHARGE OF THE BARN.

556
00:27:53,639 --> 00:27:56,642
HEY, UM. . .
SHE LIVE HERE?

557
00:27:56,708 --> 00:27:59,978
WHY. . .YOU INTERESTED?

558
00:28:00,145 --> 00:28:02,414
[both laugh]

559
00:28:02,481 --> 00:28:04,950
♪ [orchestra--
full & bright] ♪

560
00:28:05,017 --> 00:28:16,795
♪  ♪

561
00:28:16,862 --> 00:28:18,430
WHAT ARE YOU
GUYS DOIN' HERE?

562
00:28:18,497 --> 00:28:21,800
SCIENCE EXPERIMENT
BLEW UP MY SCHOOL.

563
00:28:21,867 --> 00:28:24,570
ROBBERY--
ARMED ROBBERY!

564
00:28:24,636 --> 00:28:27,739
I STOLE $1,000
AND WENT TO VEGAS.

565
00:28:29,575 --> 00:28:31,643
WHAT ABOUT YOU,
SHORT STACK?

566
00:28:32,878 --> 00:28:35,280
MY MOM LEFT ME
AT A WALMART.

567
00:28:36,048 --> 00:28:43,655
♪  ♪

568
00:28:43,722 --> 00:28:45,791
SO, MR. BANKS. . .

569
00:28:45,857 --> 00:28:47,359
SMOKEY'LL DO.

570
00:28:47,426 --> 00:28:48,827
ALL RIGHT.

571
00:28:48,894 --> 00:28:50,696
HOW LONG YA IN FOR?

572
00:28:50,762 --> 00:28:51,663
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

573
00:28:51,730 --> 00:28:53,999
I MEAN, HOW LONG
ARE YOU STUCK HERE?

574
00:28:54,066 --> 00:28:57,536
'TILL DANNY
RIDES A BULL.

575
00:28:57,603 --> 00:28:59,037
HE'S SO WEIRD.

576
00:28:59,104 --> 00:29:01,006
WEIRD ENOUGH
SO HE DIDN'T WANT

577
00:29:01,073 --> 00:29:03,342
TO GET YOU BACK FOR WHAT
YOU DID TO HIM LAST NIGHT.

578
00:29:03,408 --> 00:29:04,476
WEIRD, HUH?

579
00:29:04,543 --> 00:29:06,678
I TELL YOU
SOMETHIN',

580
00:29:06,745 --> 00:29:10,248
A GOOD COWBOY ALWAYS SLEEPS
WITH ONE EYE OPEN.

581
00:29:10,315 --> 00:29:14,319
♪  ♪

582
00:29:17,055 --> 00:29:18,056
[dog barks]

583
00:29:20,225 --> 00:29:22,861
[bed creaks]

584
00:29:22,928 --> 00:29:24,496
[dog barks]

585
00:29:29,801 --> 00:29:35,474
♪  ♪

586
00:29:35,540 --> 00:29:37,943
PERMISSION, HUH.

587
00:29:40,412 --> 00:29:41,713
[crickets chirping]

588
00:29:41,780 --> 00:29:43,515
[owl hoots]

589
00:29:43,582 --> 00:29:48,220
[door creaks]

590
00:29:48,286 --> 00:29:49,521
[click!]

591
00:29:49,588 --> 00:29:50,722
(cat)
RWOWRRR!

592
00:29:52,157 --> 00:29:54,426
OKAY, DEALER
BETS A NICKEL.

593
00:29:54,493 --> 00:29:57,162
SO YOU BET A NICKEL,

594
00:29:57,229 --> 00:30:00,065
OR ANYTHING YOU THINK
IS WORTH A NICKEL.

595
00:30:05,637 --> 00:30:07,039
YOU'RE NOT PLAYIN'?

596
00:30:07,105 --> 00:30:09,641
I DON'T PLAY
FOR MONEY.

597
00:30:09,708 --> 00:30:11,009
[chuckles]

598
00:30:11,076 --> 00:30:12,077
WUSS!

599
00:30:12,144 --> 00:30:13,645
NONE OF THAT!

600
00:30:13,712 --> 00:30:15,547
ALL COWBOYS PLAY.

601
00:30:19,918 --> 00:30:22,254
YOU CAN'T SMOKE
ON RANCH GROUNDS!!

602
00:30:22,320 --> 00:30:23,822
[boys groan]

603
00:30:25,290 --> 00:30:26,892
SHUT UP DANNY.

604
00:30:28,694 --> 00:30:30,495
LET ME TELL
YOU BOYS SOMETHIN'.

605
00:30:30,562 --> 00:30:32,097
I ONCE QUIT SMOKIN',

606
00:30:32,164 --> 00:30:35,434
DRINKIN', GAMBLIN',
AND WOMEN. . .

607
00:30:35,500 --> 00:30:38,203
IT WAS THE WORST 15 MINUTES
OF MY LIFE.

608
00:30:38,270 --> 00:30:42,207
[chuckles & laughter]

609
00:30:47,179 --> 00:30:49,915
[click, click,
click, click, click]

610
00:30:49,981 --> 00:30:54,019
♪ [acoustic flamenco guitar] ♪

611
00:30:54,086 --> 00:30:56,121
THAT MIGHT WIN NOW AT
THE LADIES' AUXILIARY

612
00:30:56,188 --> 00:30:59,324
BUT AH. . .PUT
YOUR EYES ON THESE.

613
00:30:59,391 --> 00:31:02,094
♪ [orchestral western movie
music with high trumpet lead] ♪

614
00:31:02,160 --> 00:31:04,362
THESE ARE
WHAT YOU CALL, "FACE CARDS."

615
00:31:04,429 --> 00:31:08,900
NOW SINCE ROCKY HERE DOESN'T
HAVE ANY OF 'EM. . .

616
00:31:08,967 --> 00:31:10,902
I WIN.

617
00:31:10,969 --> 00:31:12,070
♪  ♪

618
00:31:12,137 --> 00:31:13,705
TELL YOU WHAT BOYS.

619
00:31:13,772 --> 00:31:16,508
I'D HATE TO COME UP AGAINST
THIS HAND IN LAS VEGAS.

620
00:31:16,575 --> 00:31:18,744
[all groan]

621
00:31:18,810 --> 00:31:23,749
♪  ♪

622
00:31:23,815 --> 00:31:25,684
WELL. . .

623
00:31:25,751 --> 00:31:28,086
I GUESS WE BETTER
CALL IT A NIGHT.

624
00:31:28,153 --> 00:31:30,388
BUT. . .OUR MONEY.

625
00:31:30,455 --> 00:31:34,292
♪  ♪

626
00:31:34,359 --> 00:31:36,561
YOUR MONEY. . .

627
00:31:36,628 --> 00:31:39,765
♪  ♪

628
00:31:39,831 --> 00:31:42,434
THERE'S A RODEO
IN A FEW WEEKS,

629
00:31:42,501 --> 00:31:46,004
AND I UNDERSTAND I NEED
YOUR PERMISSION TO GO. . .

630
00:31:46,071 --> 00:31:49,074
AS LONG AS I'M A. . .
WHAT DO THEY CALL THAT?

631
00:31:49,141 --> 00:31:50,942
A RANCH HAND.

632
00:31:52,244 --> 00:31:56,882
RIGHT. WHY DON'T WE PLAY
FOR THAT PERMISSION?

633
00:31:56,948 --> 00:31:59,951
I DON'T THINK WE COULD
GET THAT BY MIKE.

634
00:32:00,152 --> 00:32:03,622
YOU CAN'T GET ANYTHING BY MIKE.

635
00:32:03,688 --> 00:32:04,689
[click]

636
00:32:07,459 --> 00:32:09,127
WHAT. . .

637
00:32:09,194 --> 00:32:11,296
WHAT'S WRONG?

638
00:32:11,363 --> 00:32:13,298
IT'S QUIET.

639
00:32:16,268 --> 00:32:18,436
IT'S MIDNIGHT.

640
00:32:18,503 --> 00:32:20,739
IT'S SUPPOSED TO
BE QUIET.

641
00:32:20,806 --> 00:32:23,608
IT'S TOO QUIET.

642
00:32:24,910 --> 00:32:27,245
(chuckling)
4 JACKS. . .

643
00:32:27,312 --> 00:32:28,513
NOW GIVE ME
BACK MY MONEY.

644
00:32:28,580 --> 00:32:30,048
AH, AH, AH, AH. . .

645
00:32:30,115 --> 00:32:31,716
4 KINGS.

646
00:32:31,783 --> 00:32:34,286
OH MAN!

647
00:32:34,352 --> 00:32:35,887
♪  ♪

648
00:32:35,954 --> 00:32:37,956
SEE YOU BOYS
AT THE RODEO.

649
00:32:38,023 --> 00:32:40,225
YOU DON'T HAVE
MY PERMISSION.

650
00:32:41,693 --> 00:32:43,161
OH C'MON NOW,

651
00:32:43,228 --> 00:32:46,765
THAT HAND WAS PLAYED
ON BEHALF OF ALL YOU GUYS.

652
00:32:48,500 --> 00:32:50,769
I PLAY MY OWN HAND.

653
00:32:50,836 --> 00:32:58,143
♪  ♪

654
00:32:58,210 --> 00:33:01,279
WELL, WHAT DO YOU HAVE TO PLAY
WITH THERE, PARTNER?

655
00:33:01,346 --> 00:33:04,983
WELL, THE 50 CENTS YOU OWE
ME FROM THE SODA MACHINE,

656
00:33:05,050 --> 00:33:08,119
WELL, AND MY PERMISSION
TO LET YOU GO TO THE RODEO.

657
00:33:08,186 --> 00:33:11,857
THAT AGAINST EVERYTHING
YOU WON FROM THE GUYS.

658
00:33:11,923 --> 00:33:14,526
ALL RIGHT. . .

659
00:33:14,593 --> 00:33:16,561
ALL RIGHT.

660
00:33:18,463 --> 00:33:20,365
HEY--DENNIS DEALS.

661
00:33:20,432 --> 00:33:31,042
♪  ♪

662
00:33:31,109 --> 00:33:34,613
[flapping of cards
being shuffled]

663
00:33:34,679 --> 00:33:37,949
GENTLEMEN. . .
FOR THE FARM.

664
00:33:38,049 --> 00:33:39,885
[crickets chirping]

665
00:33:39,951 --> 00:33:41,786
[owl hooting]

666
00:33:41,853 --> 00:33:51,830
♪  ♪

667
00:33:51,897 --> 00:33:53,999
♪ [music swells] ♪

668
00:33:54,065 --> 00:33:57,636
♪  ♪

669
00:33:57,702 --> 00:33:59,771
TWO, PLEASE.

670
00:33:59,838 --> 00:34:14,686
♪  ♪

671
00:34:14,753 --> 00:34:16,755
I THINK
I GOT YA KID.

672
00:34:16,821 --> 00:34:17,722
♪  ♪

673
00:34:17,789 --> 00:34:19,524
RAISE!

674
00:34:19,591 --> 00:34:20,926
WITH WHAT?

675
00:34:20,992 --> 00:34:23,595
YOU TEACH ME HOW
TO RIDE A BULL.

676
00:34:23,662 --> 00:34:25,563
WELL, I ALREADY
GOTTA DO THAT.

677
00:34:25,630 --> 00:34:27,999
NO--REALLY TEACH ME.

678
00:34:28,066 --> 00:34:30,902
NO COMPLAININ',
NO MOANIN',

679
00:34:30,969 --> 00:34:32,904
NO LOOKIN' AT LINNETTE.

680
00:34:32,971 --> 00:34:35,006
NO WANTIN' TO
QUIT ALL THE TIME.

681
00:34:35,073 --> 00:34:37,042
YOU HAVE TO
REALLY TRAIN ME.

682
00:34:37,108 --> 00:34:39,444
WHAT HAPPENS
IF YOU LOSE?

683
00:34:39,511 --> 00:34:41,379
YOU LEAVE
WHENEVER YOU WANT.

684
00:34:41,446 --> 00:34:43,348
FOR GOOD.

685
00:34:43,415 --> 00:34:46,952
♪  ♪

686
00:34:47,018 --> 00:34:48,820
ALL RIGHT. . .

687
00:34:48,887 --> 00:34:51,356
RAISE AGAIN.

688
00:34:51,423 --> 00:34:52,624
COME ON!

689
00:34:53,925 --> 00:34:56,328
AFTER THE RODEO
THERE'S A MEETING--

690
00:34:56,394 --> 00:34:58,396
COWBOY CHAPEL.

691
00:34:58,463 --> 00:34:59,898
I WANNA GO.

692
00:34:59,965 --> 00:35:02,801
EVERYBODY HAS TO
AGREE TO GO.

693
00:35:04,102 --> 00:35:06,638
I ESPECIALLY WANT
YOU TO GO.

694
00:35:09,641 --> 00:35:11,710
WHAT IF I DON'T
AGREE TO THAT?

695
00:35:12,978 --> 00:35:14,980
FOLD AND
LOOSE EVERYTHING.

696
00:35:16,815 --> 00:35:19,184
READ 'EM AND WEEP.

697
00:35:19,250 --> 00:35:34,065
♪  ♪

698
00:35:34,132 --> 00:35:36,668
ACES OVER 8s.

699
00:35:36,735 --> 00:35:39,537
GIVE ALL THE GUYS
THEY'RE MONEY BACK.

700
00:35:39,604 --> 00:35:42,374
[cheering, hooting,
and hollering]

701
00:35:42,440 --> 00:35:49,114
♪  ♪

702
00:35:49,180 --> 00:35:52,717
[the boys talking loudly]

703
00:35:52,784 --> 00:35:53,985
YEAH!

704
00:35:54,052 --> 00:35:55,553
ALL RIGHT DANNY!

705
00:35:55,620 --> 00:35:58,556
I THOUGHT YOU SAID
YOU DIDN'T GAMBLE.

706
00:35:58,623 --> 00:36:00,825
I SAID I DON'T
PLAY FOR MONEY.

707
00:36:00,892 --> 00:36:05,130
IN LIFE. . .
EVERYDAY'S A GAMBLE.

708
00:36:06,264 --> 00:36:07,899
[bell rings]

709
00:36:08,900 --> 00:36:11,302
[all talking]

710
00:36:20,745 --> 00:36:23,214
SO. . .WHAT YOU
BEEN UP TO?

711
00:36:23,281 --> 00:36:26,584
OH, I WAS JUST TEACHING THE BOYS
ABOUT THE EVILS OF GAMBLIN'.

712
00:36:28,887 --> 00:36:32,123
DID IT WORK?

713
00:36:32,190 --> 00:36:34,592
[smacks his lips]. . .YEAH.

714
00:36:39,497 --> 00:36:41,466
[rooster calling]

715
00:36:41,533 --> 00:36:43,368
[knock, knock, knock]

716
00:36:47,238 --> 00:36:49,274
WE HAVE A DEAL.

717
00:36:53,011 --> 00:36:55,914
OH! YOU GOTTA BE KIDDING ME!

718
00:36:57,816 --> 00:36:59,284
[louder knocking]

719
00:36:59,350 --> 00:37:01,753
[door creaks]

720
00:37:01,820 --> 00:37:04,756
HELLO MR. BANKS, WE'RE
WASTIN' GOOD DAYLIGHT.

721
00:37:04,823 --> 00:37:06,691
[loud sigh]

722
00:37:06,758 --> 00:37:08,493
ALL RIGHT.

723
00:37:10,695 --> 00:37:13,732
(Smokey)
IF WE'RE GONNA DO THIS AT ALL,
WE'RE GONNA DO IT RIGHT.

724
00:37:13,798 --> 00:37:16,134
LET'S START WITH
THE FUNDAMENTALS.

725
00:37:16,201 --> 00:37:18,136
WE AIN'T GOT
MUCH TO WORK WITH SO

726
00:37:18,203 --> 00:37:20,138
WE'LL HAVE TO MAKE
DUE WITH WHAT WE GOT.

727
00:37:20,205 --> 00:37:23,308
I WANT YOU TO IMAGINE
THIS IS 1800 POUNDS.

728
00:37:23,374 --> 00:37:25,477
OF REAL ANGRY FLESH
UNDER YOUR BUTT,

729
00:37:25,543 --> 00:37:29,347
100% U.S.D.A. PRIME MEAN!

730
00:37:29,414 --> 00:37:32,450
NOW THE KEY IS BELIEVIN' YOU'RE
IN CONTROL AT ALL TIMES.

731
00:37:33,384 --> 00:37:34,853
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

732
00:37:36,221 --> 00:37:39,224
WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
"WHAT WE GOT?"

733
00:37:39,290 --> 00:37:42,961
WELL, BELIEVE THAT
THIS BARREL IS A BULL,

734
00:37:43,027 --> 00:37:44,429
STUFF LIKE THAT.

735
00:37:46,798 --> 00:37:49,167
THAT'S THE WAY ALL
BULL RIDERS START OUT, SON.

736
00:37:50,101 --> 00:37:51,503
ALL RIGHT.

737
00:37:52,170 --> 00:37:54,939
UNLESS YOU CAN PULL
SOMETHIN' OUT OF YOUR HAT.

738
00:37:55,006 --> 00:37:57,842
THIS IS A BULL!

739
00:37:57,909 --> 00:38:00,912
HEY, I GOT AN IDEA--

740
00:38:00,979 --> 00:38:03,481
LET'S PRAY FOR ONE.

741
00:38:03,581 --> 00:38:08,186
DEAR GOD, PLEASE GIVE
THIS BRAT A BULL!

742
00:38:09,387 --> 00:38:11,089
HEY MR. BANKS, DANNY,

743
00:38:11,156 --> 00:38:13,725
C'MON--MIKE WANTS YOU GUYS
OUT FRONT RIGHT AWAY.

744
00:38:13,792 --> 00:38:15,226
[breathing excitedly]

745
00:38:15,293 --> 00:38:20,231
[birds chirping]

746
00:38:25,036 --> 00:38:27,238
THANKS SMOKEY.

747
00:38:29,407 --> 00:38:32,710
HOW LONG AGO DID
YOU ARRANGE FOR THAT?

748
00:38:32,777 --> 00:38:34,679
JUST SHOWED
UP, WHY?

749
00:38:37,048 --> 00:38:39,150
NO REASON.

750
00:38:40,318 --> 00:38:42,720
WELL FIRST THINGS FIRST.

751
00:38:42,787 --> 00:38:45,957
THIS IS A TOY--USED IN BARS

752
00:38:46,024 --> 00:38:48,092
BY A BUNCH
OF DRUNK WANNABEs--

753
00:38:48,159 --> 00:38:50,261
NOT BULL RIDERS.

754
00:38:50,328 --> 00:38:52,730
BUT IF THE GOOD LORD
GAVE IT TO US,

755
00:38:52,797 --> 00:38:54,933
WHO AM I TO ARGUE?

756
00:38:54,999 --> 00:38:57,368
LET ME SEE YOUR SOCKS.

757
00:38:57,435 --> 00:38:58,703
WHY?

758
00:38:58,770 --> 00:39:00,872
C'MON, LET ME
SEE 'EM.

759
00:39:00,939 --> 00:39:03,808
EVERYONE KNOWS A COWBOY
NEVER WEARS MATCHING SOCKS

760
00:39:03,875 --> 00:39:05,176
WHEN HE RIDES.

761
00:39:05,243 --> 00:39:06,878
JUST REMEMBER DANNY,

762
00:39:06,945 --> 00:39:09,314
ALWAYS RIDE A BULL
JUMP FOR JUMP.

763
00:39:09,380 --> 00:39:11,449
NEVER TRY TO TRAP 'EM,

764
00:39:11,516 --> 00:39:13,618
NEVER GET CAUGHT DOWN
INSIDE THE WELL.

765
00:39:13,685 --> 00:39:17,288
MOST IMPORTANT, ALWAYS
EXPECT THE UNEXPECTED.

766
00:39:17,355 --> 00:39:18,323
[click]

767
00:39:18,389 --> 00:39:19,057
UGH!

768
00:39:19,123 --> 00:39:20,191
[splat!!]

769
00:39:20,258 --> 00:39:21,392
OOF!

770
00:39:21,459 --> 00:39:22,994
WHOO!

771
00:39:23,061 --> 00:39:24,796
[both laughing]

772
00:39:24,862 --> 00:39:26,898
OH--IT'S GOT SPUNK!!

773
00:39:26,965 --> 00:39:28,566
HEY, THAT
WAS GREAT.

774
00:39:28,633 --> 00:39:29,601
WHOO!

775
00:39:40,879 --> 00:39:42,080
OKAY.

776
00:39:42,146 --> 00:39:43,348
THAT'S
GOOD.

777
00:39:43,414 --> 00:39:44,983
I'M ON?

778
00:39:45,049 --> 00:39:46,884
OKAY.

779
00:39:46,951 --> 00:39:48,920
(Smokey)
OKAY, HERE WE GO.

780
00:39:49,454 --> 00:39:51,356
READY?

781
00:39:51,422 --> 00:39:52,657
[click]

782
00:39:52,724 --> 00:39:56,794
[scraping of metal
gears in bull]

783
00:39:56,861 --> 00:39:58,463
(Smokey)
LOOKIN' GOOD THERE SLIM.

784
00:39:58,529 --> 00:40:00,198
LOOKIN' GOOD.

785
00:40:03,468 --> 00:40:06,104
[footsteps]

786
00:40:08,206 --> 00:40:10,508
YOU WANTED
TO SEE ME?

787
00:40:10,575 --> 00:40:12,644
YES--JUST WANTED
TO TELL YOU

788
00:40:12,710 --> 00:40:14,412
YOU'RE DOIN'
A GREAT JOB.

789
00:40:19,617 --> 00:40:22,987
THAT'S IT. JUST WANTED
TO SAY THANK YOU.

790
00:40:26,891 --> 00:40:29,093
YOU'RE WELCOME.

791
00:40:33,698 --> 00:40:35,767
HEY. . .

792
00:40:37,368 --> 00:40:40,972
YOU KNOW WHERE I CAN GET ONE OF
THOSE AH,  SWEDISH MASSAGES?

793
00:40:41,039 --> 00:40:43,341
SWEDEN?

794
00:40:47,745 --> 00:40:49,714
[birds chirping]

795
00:40:49,781 --> 00:40:51,783
[loud whinny]

796
00:40:53,484 --> 00:40:55,653
[birds chirping]

797
00:40:55,720 --> 00:40:57,855
WELL THIS IS A CHANGE.

798
00:40:57,922 --> 00:40:59,190
WHERE YOU BEEN?

799
00:40:59,257 --> 00:41:01,426
I HAD TO SEE
THE NURSE.

800
00:41:03,461 --> 00:41:04,862
YOU ALL RIGHT?

801
00:41:04,929 --> 00:41:07,031
A COWBOY'S ALWAYS
ALL RIGHT.

802
00:41:07,098 --> 00:41:09,067
LET'S GET TO IT.

803
00:41:10,935 --> 00:41:19,210
♪ [strings] ♪

804
00:41:19,277 --> 00:41:21,279
♪ [horns join the strings] ♪

805
00:41:21,346 --> 00:41:23,247
♪  ♪

806
00:41:23,314 --> 00:41:25,416
YEAH!

807
00:41:25,483 --> 00:41:28,186
♪  ♪

808
00:41:28,252 --> 00:41:30,288
WHOA!!
AH. . .

809
00:41:30,355 --> 00:41:45,970
♪  ♪

810
00:41:46,037 --> 00:41:47,872
LET IT BE.

811
00:41:47,939 --> 00:41:51,676
♪  ♪

812
00:41:51,743 --> 00:41:53,411
MY HAT.

813
00:41:53,478 --> 00:42:02,754
♪  ♪

814
00:42:02,820 --> 00:42:05,123
WHAT'S THE MATTER SON?

815
00:42:06,657 --> 00:42:08,626
YOU REALLY WANT
TO KNOW?

816
00:42:08,693 --> 00:42:10,561
WELL, I ASKED,
DIDN'T I?

817
00:42:15,033 --> 00:42:16,267
YEAH.

818
00:42:16,334 --> 00:42:18,736
ARE YOU SICK?

819
00:42:21,172 --> 00:42:23,608
YEAH.

820
00:42:23,674 --> 00:42:25,443
HOW BAD?

821
00:42:27,245 --> 00:42:29,680
NOT GOOD.

822
00:42:34,585 --> 00:42:36,988
THEY DON'T KNOW
ABOUT IT, DO THEY?

823
00:42:40,058 --> 00:42:42,226
ONLY MIKE, ELLEN,

824
00:42:42,293 --> 00:42:45,363
LINNETTE,
AND GOD.

825
00:42:45,430 --> 00:42:47,465
AND ABOUT 10
OTHER DOCTORS.

826
00:42:47,532 --> 00:42:49,934
AND I GUESS
YOU KNOW NOW.

827
00:42:50,835 --> 00:42:52,470
I'M SORRY.

828
00:42:52,537 --> 00:42:54,439
HEY C'MON. . .

829
00:42:54,505 --> 00:42:56,474
LET'S GET IT GOIN'.

830
00:42:58,176 --> 00:42:59,143
OKAY.

831
00:43:03,381 --> 00:43:05,783
WHY DIDN'T
YOU TELL ME!?

832
00:43:05,850 --> 00:43:09,053
YOU WOULDN'T
HAVE DONE IT.

833
00:43:09,120 --> 00:43:11,989
YOU STILL OWED ME
AN EXPLANATION.

834
00:43:12,056 --> 00:43:15,460
DANNY CAME TO US
THROUGH A HOPE FOUNDATION.

835
00:43:15,526 --> 00:43:21,032
I GUESS SOMEONE HEARD ABOUT US
AND THOUGHT, "OH BOYS RANCH."

836
00:43:21,098 --> 00:43:26,370
ONCE WE MET HIM THOUGH, WE KNEW
WE WERE MEANT TO BE HIS HOME.

837
00:43:26,437 --> 00:43:28,406
I'M SORRY MIKE,

838
00:43:28,473 --> 00:43:30,374
THIS JUST AIN'T
GONNA WORK OUT.

839
00:43:30,441 --> 00:43:32,877
I DON'T WANT TO BE
A PART OF THIS. . .

840
00:43:32,944 --> 00:43:35,146
THIS. . .
THIS WHOLE THING.

841
00:43:35,213 --> 00:43:37,081
IT'S A BIG MISTAKE!!!

842
00:43:37,148 --> 00:43:40,585
OKAY. I'LL CALL HANK
IN THE MORNING.

843
00:43:40,651 --> 00:43:43,588
I'LL TELL HIM
YOU'RE FREE TO GO,

844
00:43:43,654 --> 00:43:47,592
AND THANK YOU AGAIN

845
00:43:47,658 --> 00:43:49,894
FOR WHAT YOU DID
WHILE YOU WERE HERE.

846
00:43:51,596 --> 00:43:53,431
YOU'RE WELCOME.

847
00:44:03,107 --> 00:44:05,910
WE'LL SAY GOOD-BYE
TO HIM FOR YA.

848
00:44:12,950 --> 00:44:15,686
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA SAY?

849
00:44:16,954 --> 00:44:19,223
WHAT DO YOU WANT
ME TO SAY?

850
00:44:20,558 --> 00:44:21,792
[sighs]

851
00:44:39,544 --> 00:44:42,713
SOME GOD YOU SERVE,
MR. STILLWELL.

852
00:44:44,148 --> 00:44:46,651
IF I SEE HIM
ON JUDGEMENT DAY,

853
00:44:46,717 --> 00:44:48,886
I'LL LOOK HIM
RIGHT IN THE EYE,

854
00:44:48,953 --> 00:44:51,422
AND I'LL ASK HIM
ONE QUESTION. . .

855
00:44:51,489 --> 00:44:53,558
"WHY?"

856
00:44:53,624 --> 00:44:55,560
BECAUSE IF HE CAN DO THAT

857
00:44:55,626 --> 00:44:58,196
TO AN INNOCENT
LITTLE BOY LIKE DANNY,

858
00:44:58,262 --> 00:45:02,900
WHY WOULD ANYBODY WANT TO
SPEND ETERNITY WITH HIM?

859
00:45:02,967 --> 00:45:04,802
[loud smashing sounds]

860
00:45:09,707 --> 00:45:10,675
[slam!!]

861
00:45:19,650 --> 00:45:21,719
WHERE YA GOIN'
COWBOY?

862
00:45:21,786 --> 00:45:23,454
WITH ALL DUE
RESPECT LINNETTE--

863
00:45:23,521 --> 00:45:25,022
SHUT UP!!

864
00:45:32,363 --> 00:45:34,298
[breathing anxiously]

865
00:45:42,039 --> 00:45:43,341
[knock,
knock,
knock]

866
00:45:44,842 --> 00:45:47,044
THAT'S IT?. . .

867
00:45:47,111 --> 00:45:48,946
QUITTIN'?

868
00:45:49,013 --> 00:45:50,481
GET OUT!

869
00:45:51,549 --> 00:45:54,218
THEN LET
ME HELP YOU.

870
00:46:00,758 --> 00:46:03,261
HAVE TO DO WHAT IS
SO MUCH MORE IMPORTANT

871
00:46:03,327 --> 00:46:06,263
THAN HELPIN' THIS
LITTLE BOY RIDE.

872
00:46:06,330 --> 00:46:09,967
MAN, YOU SURE MUST BE
IN SOME KIND OF RUSH.

873
00:46:11,869 --> 00:46:12,837
[splat]

874
00:46:15,339 --> 00:46:18,776
NONE OF YOU HAVE GOT THE RIGHT
TO MAKE ME GO THROUGH ALL THIS.

875
00:46:21,479 --> 00:46:23,447
THERE HE IS. . .

876
00:46:23,514 --> 00:46:25,850
THE LONE COWBOY.

877
00:46:25,916 --> 00:46:28,519
THE MAN WHO
WON THE WEST. . .

878
00:46:28,586 --> 00:46:30,655
OUT ON HIS OWN.

879
00:46:32,723 --> 00:46:34,325
ONE THING'S
FOR SURE.

880
00:46:34,392 --> 00:46:36,460
I'LL DO A WHOLE LOT
BETTER ON MY OWN--

881
00:46:36,527 --> 00:46:37,495
ELSEWHERE!!--

882
00:46:37,561 --> 00:46:39,563
THAN BEIN' WITH
Y'ALL OUT HERE.

883
00:46:39,630 --> 00:46:40,731
YEAH??

884
00:46:40,798 --> 00:46:43,801
WHERE IS ELSEWHERE?

885
00:46:43,868 --> 00:46:46,203
THE NEXT BAR
DOWN THE ROAD?

886
00:46:54,178 --> 00:46:55,746
[all laughing]

887
00:46:55,813 --> 00:46:58,949
♪ [female country singer sings
"I Fall to Pieces"
in background] ♪

888
00:46:59,016 --> 00:47:01,218
(Honeycut)
HE'S THE BEST
THE SPORT'S EVER SEEN,

889
00:47:01,285 --> 00:47:04,021
RIDIN' THE BEST BULL
IN FRONT OF THE LARGEST CROWD.

890
00:47:04,088 --> 00:47:06,857
AND WINNIN' MORE MONEY
THAN YOU EVER SEEN.

891
00:47:06,924 --> 00:47:09,193
AND SPENDIN'
MORE TOO.

892
00:47:09,260 --> 00:47:10,861
WHY IF THE SPORT DIED TOMORROW,

893
00:47:10,928 --> 00:47:12,596
AIN'T NOBODY EVER RODE A BULL

894
00:47:12,663 --> 00:47:15,332
BETTER 'N SMOKEY RODE
DIZZY DEAN THAT DAY.

895
00:47:15,399 --> 00:47:18,436
C'MON SMOKEY, TELL US
ABOUT THAT RIDE ONE MORE TIME.

896
00:47:18,502 --> 00:47:23,174
WELL, I HAVE TO GIVE THAT
OLD BULL SOME CREDIT.

897
00:47:23,240 --> 00:47:26,010
HE WAS A SMART ONE.

898
00:47:26,077 --> 00:47:28,112
YOU SEE, HE CAME
OUT OF THAT SHOOT

899
00:47:28,179 --> 00:47:30,214
JUST A'SPINNIN' AND A'KICKIN'

900
00:47:30,281 --> 00:47:31,949
AS HARD AS HE COULD,

901
00:47:32,016 --> 00:47:33,584
BUT I WAS RIGHT THERE.

902
00:47:33,651 --> 00:47:35,586
I WAS RIGHT THERE
WAITIN' FOR IT.

903
00:47:35,653 --> 00:47:37,922
YA KNOW IF I HADN'T BEEN
WAITIN' FOR THAT REVERSE,

904
00:47:37,988 --> 00:47:40,224
HE WOULD HAVE THROWN ME
RIGHT OUTTA THE ARENA.

905
00:47:40,291 --> 00:47:41,325
BUT HE DIDN'T!

906
00:47:41,392 --> 00:47:42,860
NO HE DIDN'T.

907
00:47:42,927 --> 00:47:45,062
NAWWWW.

908
00:47:45,129 --> 00:47:47,598
WHAT IF HE'D SPRUNG
THE OTHER WAY?

909
00:47:47,665 --> 00:47:50,568
WELL, THEN I GUESS
I'D JUST BE SOME

910
00:47:50,634 --> 00:47:53,771
OLD, OVER-THE-HILL
DRUNK SITTIN' IN A BAR.

911
00:47:53,871 --> 00:47:55,172
♪  ♪

912
00:47:55,239 --> 00:48:00,544
[all laugh]

913
00:48:00,611 --> 00:48:02,947
NOW HOW LONG AGO
WAS THAT SMOKEY?

914
00:48:03,013 --> 00:48:04,148
♪  ♪

915
00:48:04,215 --> 00:48:06,217
OH WELL POP'S,
IF I WAVE AT YA,

916
00:48:06,283 --> 00:48:07,852
WAVE BACK AT ME,
ALL RIGHT?

917
00:48:07,918 --> 00:48:09,186
SURE SMOKEY.

918
00:48:09,253 --> 00:48:10,654
THAT'A BOY.

919
00:48:10,721 --> 00:48:13,891
♪  ♪

920
00:48:13,958 --> 00:48:15,559
HELLO DARLIN'.

921
00:48:15,626 --> 00:48:17,027
♪  ♪

922
00:48:17,094 --> 00:48:19,563
WHO ARE YOU
CALLIN' DARLIN'?

923
00:48:19,630 --> 00:48:21,932
YOU I GUESS.

924
00:48:21,999 --> 00:48:23,701
♪  ♪

925
00:48:23,768 --> 00:48:25,703
BARTENDER, ANOTHER ROUND
FOR THE BOOTH

926
00:48:25,770 --> 00:48:28,205
AND WHATEVER
MY FRIENDS HERE ARE HAVIN'.

927
00:48:28,272 --> 00:48:29,473
♪  ♪

928
00:48:29,540 --> 00:48:32,676
SAY, AREN'T YOU THAT
PIA PICANTE MAN?

929
00:48:32,743 --> 00:48:34,378
SURE AM.

930
00:48:34,445 --> 00:48:37,515
YEAH, THAT SALSA
DELICIOSO GUY?

931
00:48:37,581 --> 00:48:38,749
IN THE FLESH.

932
00:48:38,816 --> 00:48:39,884
♪  ♪

933
00:48:39,950 --> 00:48:42,319
THAT'D BE 8 BUCKS.

934
00:48:42,386 --> 00:48:45,589
OH AH, SEE THAT OLD
COWBOY OVER THERE?

935
00:48:45,656 --> 00:48:46,924
♪  ♪

936
00:48:46,991 --> 00:48:49,059
PUT IT ON HIS TAB.

937
00:48:49,126 --> 00:48:51,762
♪  ♪

938
00:48:51,829 --> 00:48:52,997
[loud smash]

939
00:48:53,063 --> 00:48:54,165
♪  ♪

940
00:48:54,231 --> 00:48:56,934
WHAT, MR. PIA
PICA PICANTE

941
00:48:57,001 --> 00:48:58,769
MAKES YOU THINK THAT

942
00:48:58,836 --> 00:49:00,905
I'D LIKE TO
DRINK WITH YOU?

943
00:49:00,971 --> 00:49:02,540
♪ ...FALL TO PIECES ♪

944
00:49:02,606 --> 00:49:05,609
YOU KNOW NORMALLY
I JUST AH, WALK AWAY,

945
00:49:05,676 --> 00:49:08,646
BUT THINGS JUST HAVEN'T BEEN
THAT NORMAL LATELY.

946
00:49:08,712 --> 00:49:09,680
SO?

947
00:49:09,747 --> 00:49:10,915
SO, I GUESS
I JUST BELIEVE

948
00:49:10,981 --> 00:49:12,550
IN GETTIN' EVERYTHING
OVER WITH AT ONCE.

949
00:49:12,616 --> 00:49:14,451
YOU KNOW WHAT COMES NEXT.

950
00:49:14,518 --> 00:49:15,553
[smack]

951
00:49:15,619 --> 00:49:16,587
[smack!!]

952
00:49:18,122 --> 00:49:19,490
SO DO YOU.

953
00:49:20,558 --> 00:49:23,627
[smashing sounds]

954
00:49:23,694 --> 00:49:24,695
UGH!!

955
00:49:24,762 --> 00:49:26,030
AAHHH!

956
00:49:27,131 --> 00:49:28,766
[truck horn honks]

957
00:49:28,833 --> 00:49:30,534
♪ BUT EACH TIME ♪

958
00:49:30,601 --> 00:49:32,536
♪ I GO OUT ♪

959
00:49:32,603 --> 00:49:34,939
[loud banging]
♪ WITH SOMEONE NEW ♪

960
00:49:35,005 --> 00:49:36,674
♪ YOU WALK BY ♪

961
00:49:36,740 --> 00:49:39,143
I AIN'T THROUGH
WITH YOU.

962
00:49:39,210 --> 00:49:40,644
AAAAAAAA!!

963
00:49:40,711 --> 00:49:43,380
♪ AND I FALL TO PIECES. ♪

964
00:49:43,447 --> 00:49:45,449
[loud smashing sounds]

965
00:49:45,516 --> 00:49:47,551
♪ YOU WALK BY ♪

966
00:49:47,618 --> 00:49:52,323
♪ AND I FALL TO PIECES ♪

967
00:49:52,389 --> 00:49:54,692
♪  ♪♪

968
00:49:55,893 --> 00:49:58,162
I KNEW YOU'D COME BACK.

969
00:49:58,229 --> 00:50:02,733
[birds chirping]

970
00:50:05,402 --> 00:50:07,738
I WONDER WHAT THE
OTHER GUYS LOOK LIKE.

971
00:50:07,805 --> 00:50:09,006
[chuckling]

972
00:50:09,073 --> 00:50:10,541
HEY DANNY, (chuckles)

973
00:50:10,608 --> 00:50:12,710
LOOKS LIKE HE TURNED
THE OTHER CHEEK ALL RIGHT.

974
00:50:12,776 --> 00:50:14,378
[all chuckle]

975
00:50:14,445 --> 00:50:15,613
BOYS. . .

976
00:50:15,679 --> 00:50:17,281
WHY DON'T YOU GO ON OUTSIDE.

977
00:50:17,348 --> 00:50:18,415
YOU CAN SEE HIM LATER.

978
00:50:18,482 --> 00:50:19,350
LET HIM REST.

979
00:50:26,490 --> 00:50:28,692
YOU KNOW, THEY
IDENTIFIED YOU

980
00:50:28,759 --> 00:50:31,528
BY THE RANCH'S LAUNDRY STAMP
ON YOUR UNDERWEAR.

981
00:50:31,595 --> 00:50:32,696
[painful laugh]

982
00:50:34,031 --> 00:50:37,101
OKAY, I'LL
BE BACK LATER.

983
00:50:42,306 --> 00:50:43,641
WHOAAA!

984
00:50:45,142 --> 00:50:47,311
HE'S ALREADY BEEN
BEAT UP ONCE.

985
00:50:47,378 --> 00:50:49,280
WHAT'S THAT GOT
TO DO WITH ME?

986
00:50:49,346 --> 00:50:51,916
WELL, JUST TRY
AND REMEMBER HOW YOU FELT

987
00:50:51,982 --> 00:50:53,817
WHEN YOU FIRST CAME HERE.

988
00:50:53,884 --> 00:50:56,153
BE NICE.

989
00:50:56,220 --> 00:51:00,791
[birds chirping]

990
00:51:00,791 --> 00:51:02,059
[loud exhale]

991
00:51:09,967 --> 00:51:12,970
KINDA LOOKS LIKE SOMEBODY
GOT THEIR CLOCK CLEANED.

992
00:51:13,037 --> 00:51:16,840
I'M NOT SURPRISED. . .
NOT IN THE LEAST.

993
00:51:23,414 --> 00:51:25,783
AS SOON AS YOU'RE
ABLE TO WALK,

994
00:51:25,849 --> 00:51:28,218
YOU'RE EITHER GONNA HELP DANNY
LEARN HOW TO RIDE BULL

995
00:51:28,285 --> 00:51:29,987
OR LEAVE IMMEDIATELY.

996
00:51:31,388 --> 00:51:34,325
IF YOU STAY, YOUR LIFE WILL NO
LONGER BE YOUR OWN,

997
00:51:34,391 --> 00:51:36,160
AND FOR THE NEXT FEW WEEKS,

998
00:51:36,226 --> 00:51:40,331
I DON'T CARE WHAT YOU THINK,
FEEL, SEE, SAY, OR DO.

999
00:51:41,165 --> 00:51:43,634
YOU HAVE ONE LAST CHANCE

1000
00:51:43,701 --> 00:51:47,204
TO CLEAN UP YOUR MISERABLE,
ROTTEN, GOAT-STINKIN' LIFE,

1001
00:51:47,271 --> 00:51:49,940
AND PERHAPS
EVEN REDEEM YOURSELF.

1002
00:51:51,842 --> 00:51:55,346
YOU CHRISTIANS,
THINK JUST BY BEIN' PUSHY,

1003
00:51:55,412 --> 00:51:58,515
YOU CAN GET
ANYTHING YOU WANT.

1004
00:51:59,883 --> 00:52:02,219
WHO SAID I
WAS A CHRISTIAN.

1005
00:52:08,192 --> 00:52:09,793
LET ME TELL YOU SOMETHIN'

1006
00:52:09,860 --> 00:52:12,329
ABOUT THESE CHRISTIANS.

1007
00:52:12,396 --> 00:52:14,531
YOU HAVE TOTALLY SCREWED UP

1008
00:52:14,598 --> 00:52:16,767
SINCE THE FIRST DAY
YOU SET FOOT HERE.

1009
00:52:16,834 --> 00:52:18,302
AND YOU KNOW WHAT?

1010
00:52:18,369 --> 00:52:20,504
THEY STILL LOVE YOU. . .

1011
00:52:20,571 --> 00:52:22,673
I DON'T GET IT.

1012
00:52:24,775 --> 00:52:27,444
[footsteps]

1013
00:52:27,511 --> 00:52:28,679
[click]

1014
00:52:28,746 --> 00:52:30,748
[footsteps]

1015
00:52:30,814 --> 00:52:31,815
[click]

1016
00:52:31,882 --> 00:52:33,250
♪ [acoustic guitar picking] ♪

1017
00:52:33,317 --> 00:52:35,886
PRAY FOR THE HAPPINESS
OF THOSE WHO CURSE YOU.

1018
00:52:35,953 --> 00:52:39,056
IMPLORE GOD'S BLESSING
ON THOSE WHO HURT YOU.

1019
00:52:39,123 --> 00:52:41,825
♪ [strings join
the guitar] ♪

1020
00:52:41,892 --> 00:52:54,405
♪  ♪

1021
00:52:54,471 --> 00:52:56,707
RUMP UP. . .

1022
00:52:56,774 --> 00:52:58,542
ARM UP!

1023
00:52:58,609 --> 00:53:00,310
♪  ♪

1024
00:53:00,310 --> 00:53:01,678
[thump]

1025
00:53:01,745 --> 00:53:08,152
♪  ♪

1026
00:53:08,218 --> 00:53:09,920
SMOKEY!

1027
00:53:12,656 --> 00:53:14,958
I'LL TAKE OVER
MISS STILLWELL.

1028
00:53:15,025 --> 00:53:17,194
THANK YOU SMOKEY.

1029
00:53:19,730 --> 00:53:21,265
MISS STILLWELL?. . .

1030
00:53:21,765 --> 00:53:23,600
THANKS.

1031
00:53:26,070 --> 00:53:26,970
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT,

1032
00:53:27,037 --> 00:53:29,039
LET'S NOT CARRIED AWAY.

1033
00:53:29,106 --> 00:53:30,974
RULE NUMBER ONE.
COWBOYS DON'T HUG.

1034
00:53:31,041 --> 00:53:32,776
YES SIR.

1035
00:53:32,843 --> 00:53:35,012
RULE NUMBER 2--DON'T CALL ME
SIR--THAT WAS MY DADDY'S NAME.

1036
00:53:35,079 --> 00:53:37,214
NOW GET UP THERE. LET'S SEE WHAT
YOU'VE BEEN WORKIN' ON.

1037
00:53:37,281 --> 00:53:38,882
OKAY.

1038
00:53:38,949 --> 00:53:43,787
♪  ♪

1039
00:53:43,854 --> 00:53:46,623
ALL RIGHT, JUST SETTLE
DOWN NOW, RELAX.

1040
00:53:46,690 --> 00:53:49,960
DON'T GET ALL EXCITED
OVER NOTHING.

1041
00:53:50,027 --> 00:53:52,863
♪ [music swells] ♪

1042
00:53:52,930 --> 00:53:56,166
♪  ♪

1043
00:53:56,233 --> 00:53:59,937
GIT UP ON THERE.

1044
00:54:00,137 --> 00:54:01,805
DIG YOUR HEELS IN,
NOW DIG 'EM IN.

1045
00:54:01,872 --> 00:54:03,874
GOOD. POSTURE. . .
POSTURE.

1046
00:54:03,941 --> 00:54:05,442
LIKE YOU'RE
HOLDIN' A PIZZA NOW.

1047
00:54:05,509 --> 00:54:07,311
PUT YOUR HAND UP.
THAT'A BOY.

1048
00:54:07,377 --> 00:54:09,379
HEY, DID YOU
TELL HIM YET?

1049
00:54:09,446 --> 00:54:10,514
NO.

1050
00:54:10,581 --> 00:54:11,915
TELL HIM WHAT?

1051
00:54:11,982 --> 00:54:13,283
THERE'S A RODEO
OVER IN STOCKTON

1052
00:54:13,350 --> 00:54:14,651
IN ABOUT A WEEK.

1053
00:54:14,718 --> 00:54:16,353
YEAH?

1054
00:54:16,420 --> 00:54:17,955
(Mike)
YEAH, AND THIS YEAR

1055
00:54:18,021 --> 00:54:19,490
IT MIGHT BE
A LITTLE DIFFERENT.

1056
00:54:19,556 --> 00:54:21,458
WHY?

1057
00:54:21,525 --> 00:54:23,594
WELL, LITTLE JOHN'S WESTERN WEAR

1058
00:54:23,660 --> 00:54:25,963
HAS AGREED TO DONATE
SOME NEW CLOTHES

1059
00:54:26,029 --> 00:54:28,632
SO WE CAN ALL GO IN STYLE!

1060
00:54:28,699 --> 00:54:32,402
[Smokey & Mike chucking]

1061
00:54:32,469 --> 00:54:33,904
NOT FUNNY MIKE.

1062
00:54:33,971 --> 00:54:36,440
YOU KNOW COWBOYS HATE
TRYIN' ON NEW CLOTHES.

1063
00:54:36,507 --> 00:54:41,178
[birds chirping]

1064
00:54:41,245 --> 00:54:43,447
HEY, S-SOMEBODY SAY SOMETHING.

1065
00:54:43,514 --> 00:54:44,982
WELL C'MON.

1066
00:54:45,048 --> 00:54:46,817
WHAT WOULD YOU SAY
IF I TOLD YOU

1067
00:54:46,884 --> 00:54:49,019
WE ENTERED YOU
IN THE JUNIOR RODEO?

1068
00:54:49,953 --> 00:54:54,358
ME? IN A RODEO
ON A REAL BULL?

1069
00:54:54,424 --> 00:54:56,260
YOU UP TO IT?

1070
00:54:56,326 --> 00:54:58,662
AM I? YEAH.

1071
00:54:58,729 --> 00:55:01,632
HEY, AREN'T WE GONNA
NEED A BULL?

1072
00:55:01,698 --> 00:55:04,001
SAY HELLO TO LORENZO.

1073
00:55:04,067 --> 00:55:06,703
[loud bellowing
and kicking sounds]

1074
00:55:06,770 --> 00:55:08,172
[very loud bellow]

1075
00:55:09,773 --> 00:55:12,242
[loud bellow]

1076
00:55:12,309 --> 00:55:13,944
BEFORE YOU GO TO STOCKTON,

1077
00:55:14,011 --> 00:55:15,979
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE
TO RIDE HIM,

1078
00:55:17,414 --> 00:55:19,650
AND YOU'RE GONNA
HAVE TO TEACH HIM.

1079
00:55:19,716 --> 00:55:21,485
[loud bellow]

1080
00:55:21,552 --> 00:55:24,054
♪ [bright music--
full orchestra] ♪

1081
00:55:24,121 --> 00:56:05,262
♪  ♪

1082
00:56:05,329 --> 00:56:07,698
(Smokey)
ALL RIGHT,
THIS IS IT.

1083
00:56:07,764 --> 00:56:10,067
THIS IS WHAT
IT'S ALL ABOUT.

1084
00:56:10,133 --> 00:56:12,336
THE CROWD IS QUIET.

1085
00:56:12,402 --> 00:56:14,871
THE BULL TURNS AND LOOKS AT YOU
WITH A FIRE IN HIS EYE,

1086
00:56:14,938 --> 00:56:16,807
AND HE SAYS,
"I KNOW SMOKEY BANKS.

1087
00:56:16,873 --> 00:56:18,942
I KNOW TUFF HEDERMAN,

1088
00:56:19,009 --> 00:56:20,410
BUT WHO ARE YOU?"

1089
00:56:20,477 --> 00:56:21,979
YOU LOOK HIM RIGHT BACK
IN THE EYE,

1090
00:56:22,045 --> 00:56:23,213
AND YOU SAY,
"I'M DANNY O'NEILL."

1091
00:56:23,280 --> 00:56:24,514
LET'S RODEO!!

1092
00:56:24,581 --> 00:56:25,849
[everybody yelling]

1093
00:56:25,916 --> 00:56:27,751
[Lorenzo bellows]

1094
00:56:27,818 --> 00:56:30,921
[cowbell ringing]

1095
00:56:30,988 --> 00:56:34,258
DON'T JUST STAND THERE,
DO SOMETHIN'!!

1096
00:56:34,324 --> 00:56:36,994
[loud splattering--
bull relieving himself]

1097
00:56:46,937 --> 00:56:48,872
(Willie Nelson singing)
♪ MAMA, ♪

1098
00:56:48,939 --> 00:56:52,709
♪ DON'T LET YOUR BABIES
GROW UP TO BE COWBOYS. ♪

1099
00:56:52,776 --> 00:56:55,545
♪  ♪

1100
00:56:55,612 --> 00:56:57,648
♪ DON'T LET 'EM PICK GUITARS ♪

1101
00:56:57,648 --> 00:57:00,217
♪ AND DRIVE THEM OL' TRUCKS ♪

1102
00:57:00,284 --> 00:57:03,854
♪ MAKE 'EM BE DOCTORS
AND LAWYERS AND SUCH. ♪

1103
00:57:03,920 --> 00:57:05,355
♪  ♪

1104
00:57:05,422 --> 00:57:10,627
♪ MAMA, DON'T LET YOUR BABIES
GROW UP TO BE COWBOYS. ♪

1105
00:57:10,694 --> 00:57:13,130
♪  ♪

1106
00:57:13,196 --> 00:57:15,032
♪ THEY'LL NEVER STAY HOME, ♪

1107
00:57:15,098 --> 00:57:17,200
♪ AND THEY'RE ALWAYS ALONE ♪

1108
00:57:17,267 --> 00:57:21,104
♪ EVEN WITH
SOMEONE THEY LOVE. ♪

1109
00:57:21,171 --> 00:57:23,874
♪  ♪

1110
00:57:23,940 --> 00:57:26,677
♪ COWBOYS AIN'T
EASY TO LOVE,

1111
00:57:26,743 --> 00:57:29,846
♪ AND THEY'RE
HARDER TO HOLD. ♪

1112
00:57:29,913 --> 00:57:31,982
♪  ♪

1113
00:57:32,049 --> 00:57:34,885
♪ AND THEY'D RATHER
GIVE YOU A SONG ♪

1114
00:57:34,951 --> 00:57:38,188
♪ THAN DIAMONDS AND GOLD. ♪

1115
00:57:38,255 --> 00:57:40,991
♪  ♪

1116
00:57:41,058 --> 00:57:45,262
♪ MAMA, DON'T LET YOUR BABIES
GROW UP TO BE COWBOYS. ♪

1117
00:57:45,329 --> 00:57:48,832
♪  ♪

1118
00:57:48,899 --> 00:57:52,002
[talking & laughing]

1119
00:57:58,508 --> 00:58:01,345
(Mike)
COME ON, COME ON,
GET IT IN GUYS!

1120
00:58:04,247 --> 00:58:05,749
[engine starts]

1121
00:58:13,724 --> 00:58:16,059
♪ [orchestra--
minor tones] ♪

1122
00:58:21,531 --> 00:58:23,266
[crickets chirping]

1123
00:58:23,333 --> 00:58:25,102
[horse neighs]

1124
00:58:40,851 --> 00:58:42,586
[horse neighs]

1125
00:58:44,521 --> 00:58:47,624
[dog barking]

1126
00:58:54,831 --> 00:58:56,967
[whoosh]

1127
00:58:57,033 --> 00:58:58,535
[chuckles]

1128
00:59:05,675 --> 00:59:08,678
HOW COME YOU AIN'T
NEVER BEEN CAUGHT.

1129
00:59:08,745 --> 00:59:11,047
NO ONE I KNOW
HAS BEEN

1130
00:59:11,114 --> 00:59:12,582
AS GRACIOUS AS THIS.

1131
00:59:12,649 --> 00:59:14,484
IS THAT A FACT?

1132
00:59:14,551 --> 00:59:16,420
AND YOU?

1133
00:59:16,486 --> 00:59:19,356
WELL, YOU KNOW WHAT IT'S LIKE.

1134
00:59:19,423 --> 00:59:22,793
NO. . .WHAT'S IT LIKE?

1135
00:59:24,261 --> 00:59:27,931
I CAN'T THINK OF A YEAR I DIDN'T
PUT 100,000 MILES ON MY TRUCK.

1136
00:59:30,233 --> 00:59:32,068
SOUNDS LIKE AN EXCUSE.

1137
00:59:34,671 --> 00:59:37,574
UH. . .MAYBE.

1138
00:59:43,747 --> 00:59:45,549
IT'S JUST. . .

1139
00:59:45,615 --> 00:59:47,250
YOU KNOW YOU
START OUT YOUNG.

1140
00:59:47,317 --> 00:59:49,686
SOMEBODY TELLS YOU
THAT YOU'RE GOOD.

1141
00:59:51,488 --> 00:59:53,623
ONE DAY
YOU BELIEVE IT.

1142
00:59:53,690 --> 00:59:56,493
THEN YOU START WINNIN'.

1143
00:59:56,560 --> 00:59:59,062
SMALL STUFF AT FIRST,
THEN THE REGIONALS,

1144
00:59:59,129 --> 01:00:01,932
THEN THE BIG SHOW.

1145
01:00:01,998 --> 01:00:05,602
THEN WHEN YOU'VE GOT--

1146
01:00:05,669 --> 01:00:09,406
SPENT ALL THAT TIME
TRYIN' TO GET. . .

1147
01:00:11,675 --> 01:00:14,311
THAT'S IT.

1148
01:00:16,213 --> 01:00:20,283
THEN YOU SPEND THE REST OF YOUR
LIFE IN BARS.

1149
01:00:20,350 --> 01:00:23,620
GETTIN' IN FIGHTS.

1150
01:00:23,687 --> 01:00:30,126
THEM KNOWIN' YOU ON A FIRST-NAME
BASIS AT THE LOCAL JAIL.

1151
01:00:30,193 --> 01:00:32,963
YEAH. . .IT'S JUST,
ONE DAY

1152
01:00:33,029 --> 01:00:34,865
YOU NOTICE A NEW GUY,

1153
01:00:34,931 --> 01:00:37,267
A BIT YOUNGER THAN YOU--

1154
01:00:37,334 --> 01:00:40,070
DOESN'T EVEN LOOK YOUR WAY.

1155
01:00:40,136 --> 01:00:43,073
WHEN THE DUST CLEARS,

1156
01:00:43,140 --> 01:00:47,577
THEY'RE AWARDIN' HIM THE BUCKLE.

1157
01:00:47,644 --> 01:00:51,581
AND THEN YOU'VE GOT NOTHIN'

1158
01:00:51,648 --> 01:00:54,651
WELL I KNOW WHEN
I'VE OVERSTAYED MY WELCOME.

1159
01:00:56,953 --> 01:00:59,256
YOU SHOULD TRY
STAYIN' LONGER.

1160
01:00:59,322 --> 01:01:02,325
IF YOU EVER GET THE
CHANCE AGAIN, THAT IS.

1161
01:01:03,827 --> 01:01:05,962
WELL, I'M THINKIN'
ABOUT IT.

1162
01:01:06,029 --> 01:01:08,265
♪ [orchestra] ♪

1163
01:01:08,331 --> 01:01:16,840
♪  ♪

1164
01:01:16,907 --> 01:01:19,976
♪ [orchestra &
acoustic guitar] ♪

1165
01:01:20,043 --> 01:01:32,022
♪  ♪

1166
01:01:32,088 --> 01:01:33,757
[knocking]

1167
01:01:33,823 --> 01:01:36,092
COME IN.

1168
01:01:36,159 --> 01:01:37,561
[click]

1169
01:01:38,628 --> 01:01:40,664
HEY DANNY.

1170
01:01:40,730 --> 01:01:41,865
HEY.

1171
01:01:43,600 --> 01:01:45,335
WHAT'S UP?

1172
01:01:47,604 --> 01:01:49,839
WHAT ARE YOU DOIN'?

1173
01:01:49,906 --> 01:01:52,509
AW, JUST TRYIN' TO FIGURE OUT
THIS CROSSWORD PUZZLE.

1174
01:01:56,613 --> 01:01:58,748
DANNY. . .

1175
01:02:12,596 --> 01:02:14,331
YOU'RE READY.

1176
01:02:16,366 --> 01:02:19,803
WOW, THIS IS IT.

1177
01:02:19,869 --> 01:02:21,705
IT IS!

1178
01:02:21,771 --> 01:02:24,541
I WANT YOU TO HAVE THAT.

1179
01:02:27,277 --> 01:02:29,679
SMOKEY, THAT'S GREAT.

1180
01:02:29,746 --> 01:02:32,916
BUT IF YOU DON'T MIND,

1181
01:02:32,983 --> 01:02:36,052
I'D LIKE TO WIN
ONE OF MY OWN.

1182
01:02:36,119 --> 01:02:38,755
YOU WILL. . .
YOU WILL!

1183
01:02:40,657 --> 01:02:44,327
I JUST AH, WANTED
YOU TO KNOW THAT AH,

1184
01:02:44,394 --> 01:02:48,598
IN MY EYES, YOU'RE
ALREADY A WORLD'S CHAMP.

1185
01:02:51,534 --> 01:02:54,371
YOU'VE HAD TO FACE
SOME THINGS THAT AH. . .

1186
01:02:54,437 --> 01:02:57,273
NONE OF US HAVE.

1187
01:02:59,876 --> 01:03:02,312
SEE. . .

1188
01:03:02,379 --> 01:03:04,481
TONIGHT I READ
ABOUT A DIFFERENT PRIZE.

1189
01:03:04,547 --> 01:03:08,018
ONE THAT LASTS FOREVER.

1190
01:03:08,084 --> 01:03:11,755
YOU SEE, IT'S NOT
ABOUT HOW LONG I'M ON--

1191
01:03:11,821 --> 01:03:16,226
IT'S ABOUT
HOW WELL I RIDE.

1192
01:03:16,292 --> 01:03:27,303
♪  ♪

1193
01:03:27,370 --> 01:03:29,773
WHY DON'T YOU
GET SOME SLEEP.

1194
01:03:29,839 --> 01:03:30,573
♪  ♪

1195
01:03:30,573 --> 01:03:31,641
[click]

1196
01:03:31,708 --> 01:03:44,454
♪  ♪

1197
01:03:44,521 --> 01:03:46,523
[dog barks]

1198
01:03:46,589 --> 01:03:52,195
♪  ♪

1199
01:03:57,500 --> 01:04:00,303
YOU DIDN'T REALLY THINK
YOU COULD HIDE, DID YA?

1200
01:04:00,303 --> 01:04:02,639
TIME'S UP, COWBOY.

1201
01:04:02,706 --> 01:04:07,544
♪  ♪

1202
01:04:07,610 --> 01:04:08,912
WHAT DO YOU SAY

1203
01:04:08,978 --> 01:04:11,281
YOU AND ME AND MY BUDDY GO

1204
01:04:11,347 --> 01:04:13,450
FOR A LITTLE MOONLIT WALK TO MY
CAR.

1205
01:04:13,516 --> 01:04:14,150
COME ON.

1206
01:04:14,217 --> 01:04:17,353
HEY DENNIS, GO GET MIKE.

1207
01:04:20,924 --> 01:04:22,425
OUW!

1208
01:04:23,960 --> 01:04:25,962
DO YOU HAVE MY MONEY?

1209
01:04:26,029 --> 01:04:27,464
(Smokey)
NO!

1210
01:04:27,530 --> 01:04:29,199
[horse whinnies]

1211
01:04:29,265 --> 01:04:30,734
YOU'RE OUT OF OPTIONS.

1212
01:04:30,800 --> 01:04:33,937
[pounding of hooves]

1213
01:04:34,003 --> 01:05:02,031
♪  ♪

1214
01:05:02,098 --> 01:05:05,001
I'M GONNA KILL YA!

1215
01:05:10,874 --> 01:05:13,510
I WILL SAY ONE THING,
SMOKEY BANKS,

1216
01:05:13,576 --> 01:05:15,245
YOU SURE HAVE MADE THIS
AN INTERESTIN' PLACE

1217
01:05:15,311 --> 01:05:17,213
SINCE SHOWIN' UP.

1218
01:05:19,916 --> 01:05:21,551
HEY, SMOKEY.

1219
01:05:25,922 --> 01:05:28,158
SO GENTLEMEN. . .

1220
01:05:28,224 --> 01:05:31,227
SMOKEY BANKS IS
A FRIEND OF MINE.

1221
01:05:31,294 --> 01:05:34,397
WHAT WILL IT TAKE
TO SETTLE HIS INDEBTEDNESS?

1222
01:05:34,464 --> 01:05:36,699
MIKE, PLEASE, NO.

1223
01:05:38,434 --> 01:05:43,006
HOW MUCH. . .
DOES MR. BANKS OWE?

1224
01:05:43,072 --> 01:05:45,809
12 HUNDRED BUCKS.

1225
01:05:50,747 --> 01:05:53,650
WELL AROUND HERE,

1226
01:05:53,716 --> 01:05:56,686
WE BELIEVE IN RENDERING
UNTO CAESAR WHAT IS HIS,

1227
01:05:56,753 --> 01:05:59,155
EVEN WITH INTEREST AND
PENALTIES.

1228
01:06:03,660 --> 01:06:08,531
NOW. . .
WHAT WILL YOU TAKE?

1229
01:06:08,598 --> 01:06:12,068
NOT A DIME LESS THAN ALL OF IT.

1230
01:06:13,136 --> 01:06:15,538
YOU'RE SURE?

1231
01:06:15,605 --> 01:06:18,675
YOU JUST DON'T GET IT,
DO YOU BOZO?

1232
01:06:18,741 --> 01:06:21,110
YOU SEE, I WANT MY MONEY.

1233
01:06:21,177 --> 01:06:23,746
YOU DON'T HAVE
ANY OTHER OPTIONS.

1234
01:06:25,849 --> 01:06:28,685
I CAN THINK OF ONE.

1235
01:06:35,725 --> 01:06:36,993
GYAH!!!

1236
01:06:37,060 --> 01:06:41,564
[police dispatcher
on radio in distance]

1237
01:06:41,631 --> 01:06:43,533
SO YOU ROPED HIM
ON THE FEET?

1238
01:06:43,600 --> 01:06:45,301
YOU GOT HIM BY THE NECK?

1239
01:06:45,368 --> 01:06:47,704
(Smokey)
HE TURNED SO PURPLE I THOUGHT HE
WAS GOING TO BURST.

1240
01:06:47,770 --> 01:06:49,505
AREN'T YOU SMOKEY BANKS?

1241
01:06:49,572 --> 01:06:50,807
AT YOUR SERVICE.

1242
01:06:50,874 --> 01:06:52,842
YOU ARE HEREBY PLACED
UNDER ARREST

1243
01:06:52,909 --> 01:06:54,644
FOR PROPERTY DAMAGE AND AN
ASSAULT COMPLAINT.

1244
01:06:54,711 --> 01:06:56,079
YOU HAVE THE RIGHT TO REMAIN
SILENT.

1245
01:06:56,145 --> 01:06:58,548
ANYTHING YOU MAY SAY CAN AND
WILL BE USED AGAINST YOU.

1246
01:06:58,615 --> 01:07:01,284
HEY, SMOKEY DIDN'T DO ANYTHING,
DID YA SMOKEY?

1247
01:07:01,351 --> 01:07:04,520
MR. BANKS IS HERE UNDER
MY PROTECTIVE CUSTODY.

