♪  ♪

1488
01:22:23,405 --> 01:22:25,374
ADIOS AMIGO.

1489
01:22:25,441 --> 01:22:31,547
♪  ♪

1490
01:22:31,613 --> 01:22:34,683
I DON'T NEED YOU EITHER.

1491
01:22:37,286 --> 01:22:39,188
[birds chirping]

1492
01:22:39,254 --> 01:22:39,955
[slam!]

1493
01:22:40,022 --> 01:22:41,590
[whoosh!!]

1494
01:22:41,657 --> 01:22:42,991
HEY!!!

1495
01:22:43,058 --> 01:22:46,361
YIPPEE KAI YAI YAY,
SMOKEY BANKS.

1496
01:22:46,428 --> 01:22:49,731
[laughing]

1497
01:22:51,133 --> 01:22:52,701
OKAY, GUYS.

1498
01:22:52,768 --> 01:22:54,570
[clinking of fork on plate]

1499
01:22:55,938 --> 01:22:57,439
WAIT, WAIT
BEFORE WE START.

1500
01:22:57,506 --> 01:22:59,274
I HAVE TO MAKE
AN ANNOUNCEMENT.

1501
01:22:59,341 --> 01:23:00,876
THIS IS THE LAST NIGHT

1502
01:23:00,943 --> 01:23:03,045
YOU GET TO WEAR YOUR
HATS AT THE DINNER TABLE.

1503
01:23:03,111 --> 01:23:04,746
[boys chuckling]

1504
01:23:04,813 --> 01:23:07,182
(Smokey)
IT'S GROWING BACK
PRETTY GOOD.

1505
01:23:07,316 --> 01:23:08,650
OKAY GUYS.

1506
01:23:08,717 --> 01:23:11,920
HEY, NOW SMOKEY, SEEING AS
THIS IS YOUR LAST DAY,

1507
01:23:11,987 --> 01:23:14,089
WE HAVE A LITTLE
PRESENTATION FOR YOU.

1508
01:23:14,156 --> 01:23:16,191
HOW LONG YOU BEEN HERE ANYWAY?

1509
01:23:16,258 --> 01:23:18,460
IT'S BEEN AH. . .

1510
01:23:18,527 --> 01:23:20,629
ABOUT 100 YEARS.
[chuckling]

1511
01:23:20,696 --> 01:23:22,865
(Mike)
ALL THAT TIME
AND STILL A RANCH HAND.

1512
01:23:22,931 --> 01:23:25,901
SO WE DISCUSSED THIS
AMONGST OURSELVES,

1513
01:23:25,968 --> 01:23:28,637
AND WE DECIDED THAT YOU
COULD NOT LEAVE THE RANCH

1514
01:23:28,704 --> 01:23:31,974
UNLESS YOU ARE A TRAIL BOSS.

1515
01:23:32,040 --> 01:23:35,577
(all)
OOOO!!

1516
01:23:35,644 --> 01:23:37,379
HERE YA GO.
PASS IT DOWN.

1517
01:23:37,446 --> 01:23:40,148
NOW, THE PRIVILEGE THAT
COMES WITH THAT CERTIFICATE

1518
01:23:40,215 --> 01:23:42,117
IS THAT YOU GET
TO LEAVE THIS RANCH

1519
01:23:42,184 --> 01:23:45,153
ANYTIME YOU WANT--
WITHOUT PERMISSION.

1520
01:23:45,220 --> 01:23:47,990
MORE IMPORTANTLY, YOU GET
TO COME BACK ANYTIME,

1521
01:23:48,056 --> 01:23:50,325
UNANNOUNCED FOR ANY REASON,

1522
01:23:50,392 --> 01:23:53,061
AND IF THE
CIRCUMSTANCES WARRANT

1523
01:23:53,128 --> 01:23:54,563
THAT IT SEEMS
THAT YOU CAN'T

1524
01:23:54,630 --> 01:23:57,132
QUITE FIND YOUR
WAY BACK HOME. . .

1525
01:23:57,199 --> 01:23:58,300
WE'LL COME GET YOU--

1526
01:23:58,367 --> 01:24:00,669
ONLY IF YOU ARE WEARING

1527
01:24:00,736 --> 01:24:02,304
THE RANCH UNDERWEAR.

1528
01:24:02,371 --> 01:24:04,439
[everyone chuckles]

1529
01:24:04,506 --> 01:24:06,508
[applause]

1530
01:24:07,976 --> 01:24:09,511
THANK YOU. . .

1531
01:24:09,578 --> 01:24:10,913
THANK YOU.

1532
01:24:13,081 --> 01:24:14,383
I'LL TELL YOU,

1533
01:24:14,449 --> 01:24:16,818
YOU ARE A PART
OF THE RANCH FAMILY.

1534
01:24:16,885 --> 01:24:17,819
YES!!

1535
01:24:17,886 --> 01:24:24,860
[hoots, hollers,
and applause]

1536
01:24:24,927 --> 01:24:28,230
ALL RIGHT EVERYBODY,
ALL RIGHT CALM DOWN,

1537
01:24:28,297 --> 01:24:30,232
AS IF THAT'S POSSIBLE
AROUND HERE.

1538
01:24:30,299 --> 01:24:34,102
NOW WE HAVE A SPECIAL TREAT.

1539
01:24:36,104 --> 01:24:37,839
WOO, HOO, HOO, HOO!

1540
01:24:37,906 --> 01:24:39,708
MOVE THE STUFF,
MOVE THE STUFF!

1541
01:24:39,775 --> 01:24:42,244
IT'S BIGGER
THAN YOU ARE.

1542
01:24:42,311 --> 01:24:44,246
AIYEEE!!

1543
01:24:45,213 --> 01:24:47,149
WHAT'S THIS FOR?

1544
01:24:47,215 --> 01:24:48,817
(Mike)
YOU'LL SEE.

1545
01:24:48,884 --> 01:24:50,619
UM, SMOKEY,

1546
01:24:50,686 --> 01:24:53,388
WOULD YOU DO THE PRESENTATION?

1547
01:24:53,455 --> 01:24:55,791
IT'D BE MY HONOR.

1548
01:25:00,729 --> 01:25:03,065
TO DANNY O'NEIL,
A SPECIAL COMMENDATION

1549
01:25:03,131 --> 01:25:07,135
FOR RIDING IN THE JUNIOR
RODEO BULL RIDING EVENT--

1550
01:25:07,202 --> 01:25:09,638
AND STAYING ON 8 SECONDS,
I MIGHT ADD.

1551
01:25:09,705 --> 01:25:14,209
[whooping & applause]

1552
01:25:14,276 --> 01:25:15,310
YES!!

1553
01:25:15,377 --> 01:25:17,045
YEAH!!

1554
01:25:24,853 --> 01:25:27,656
GO ON DANNY,
BLOW OUT THE CANDLES.

1555
01:25:35,364 --> 01:25:37,699
HE CAN'T!

1556
01:25:45,607 --> 01:25:48,110
(dispatcher)
MEMORIAL HOSPITAL,
EMERGENCY DISPATCH.

1557
01:25:48,176 --> 01:25:49,778
(Mike)
YEAH, THIS IS MIKE STILLWELL

1558
01:25:49,845 --> 01:25:51,279
FROM THE SAGUARO BOY'S RANCH.

1559
01:25:51,346 --> 01:25:53,081
WE GOT A REAL SICK KID
IN THE CAR.

1560
01:25:53,148 --> 01:25:54,349
(dispatcher)
BRING HIM TO THE E.R.

1561
01:25:54,416 --> 01:25:55,484
HOW FAR OUT ARE YOU?

1562
01:25:55,550 --> 01:25:57,152
(Mike)
WE'LL BE THERE
IN ABOUT 10 MINUTES.

1563
01:25:57,219 --> 01:25:58,787
(dispatcher)
WE'LL BE WAITING
FOR YOU, OVER.

1564
01:25:58,854 --> 01:26:00,922
(Mike)
OKAY, OVER AND OUT.

1565
01:26:00,989 --> 01:26:21,543
♪  ♪

1566
01:26:29,451 --> 01:26:32,087
YOU MADE IT!

1567
01:26:32,154 --> 01:26:34,656
A COWBOY ALWAYS
KEEPS HIS WORD.

1568
01:26:46,334 --> 01:26:49,071
I'M REALLY GLAD
YOU'RE HERE.

1569
01:26:49,638 --> 01:26:51,840
ME TOO!

1570
01:26:51,907 --> 01:26:55,710
HEY, REMEMBER WHEN I
TOLD YOU I WASN'T SCARED?

1571
01:26:55,777 --> 01:26:58,747
THAT DAY BEFORE THE RIDE?

1572
01:26:58,814 --> 01:27:01,717
YEAH.

1573
01:27:01,783 --> 01:27:04,553
WELL, I WAS KINDA.

1574
01:27:04,619 --> 01:27:07,055
A LITTLE SCARED MAYBE.

1575
01:27:07,122 --> 01:27:09,491
A LITTLE SCARED'S GOOD.

1576
01:27:09,558 --> 01:27:11,526
SHOWS RESPECT
FOR THE BULL.

1577
01:27:12,928 --> 01:27:14,563
SMOKE?

1578
01:27:14,629 --> 01:27:16,198
YEAH?

1579
01:27:16,264 --> 01:27:18,934
AT THE RIDE
AT THE RODEO. . .

1580
01:27:19,000 --> 01:27:21,770
I CLOSED MY EYES
FOR A FEW SECONDS,

1581
01:27:21,837 --> 01:27:25,607
AND WHEN I OPENED
'EM UP AGAIN,

1582
01:27:25,674 --> 01:27:28,510
THERE Y'ALL WERE.

1583
01:27:28,577 --> 01:27:31,480
YOU, MIKE,
ELLEN, LINNETTE,

1584
01:27:31,546 --> 01:27:33,415
AND ALL THE OTHER GUYS.

1585
01:27:33,482 --> 01:27:36,017
SO WHEN I OPEN UP
MY EYES AGAIN,

1586
01:27:36,084 --> 01:27:39,387
PROMISE ME I'LL
SEE YA, OKAY?

1587
01:27:44,326 --> 01:27:46,595
I'LL DO MY BEST, KID.

1588
01:27:48,063 --> 01:27:51,133
I WANT ONE MORE THING--

1589
01:27:54,035 --> 01:27:57,038
GET BACK ON AND RIDE.

1590
01:28:04,045 --> 01:28:06,581
(with weak voice)
I'M TIRED.

1591
01:28:06,648 --> 01:28:08,850
♪ [acoustic guitar playing] ♪

1592
01:28:08,917 --> 01:28:19,594
♪  ♪

1593
01:28:19,594 --> 01:28:21,062
[sniffling]

1594
01:28:21,129 --> 01:28:30,272
♪  ♪

1595
01:28:30,338 --> 01:28:33,074
♪ [full orchestra
playing majestically] ♪

1596
01:28:33,141 --> 01:28:59,901
♪ ♪

1597
01:29:21,556 --> 01:29:24,960
GOD. . .
I NEVER UNDERSTOOD

1598
01:29:25,026 --> 01:29:27,329
WHY YOU LET THOSE GUYS
IN THE BIBLE

1599
01:29:27,395 --> 01:29:30,765
KILL YOUR SON. . .

1600
01:29:30,832 --> 01:29:33,969
OR WHY HE WENT WILLINGLY.

1601
01:29:34,035 --> 01:29:37,072
♪  ♪

1602
01:29:37,138 --> 01:29:40,342
I NEVER UNDERSTOOD WHAT IT MEANT
TO GO IN SOMEBODY'S PLACE--

1603
01:29:40,408 --> 01:29:43,278
♪  ♪

1604
01:29:43,345 --> 01:29:46,548
NEVER UNDERSTOOD
THAT AT ALL.

1605
01:29:46,615 --> 01:29:48,383
♪  ♪

1606
01:29:48,450 --> 01:29:51,319
'TILL NOW.

1607
01:29:51,386 --> 01:29:59,661
♪  ♪

1608
01:29:59,728 --> 01:30:02,364
I'M JUST A MAN.

1609
01:30:02,430 --> 01:30:05,200
NOT A VERY GOOD
ONE AT THAT.

1610
01:30:05,267 --> 01:30:06,835
♪  ♪

1611
01:30:06,901 --> 01:30:08,970
BUT GOD. . .

1612
01:30:09,037 --> 01:30:11,473
I REALLY LOVE THIS KID.

1613
01:30:11,539 --> 01:30:14,676
IF I COULD TAKE HIS PLACE,
I WOULD.

1614
01:30:14,743 --> 01:30:19,347
♪  ♪

1615
01:30:19,414 --> 01:30:22,350
I KNOW I AIN'T GOT
MUCH TO OFFER. . .

1616
01:30:22,417 --> 01:30:27,656
♪  ♪

1617
01:30:27,722 --> 01:30:30,759
BUT FROM NOW ON,

1618
01:30:30,825 --> 01:30:32,794
♪  ♪

1619
01:30:32,861 --> 01:30:36,898
WHAT I GOT IS YOURS.

1620
01:30:40,802 --> 01:30:43,772
[crying]

1621
01:30:43,838 --> 01:31:01,289
♪  ♪

1622
01:31:01,356 --> 01:31:05,727
♪ [orchestral--
dissonant & suspenseful] ♪

1623
01:31:05,794 --> 01:31:19,240
♪  ♪

1624
01:31:19,307 --> 01:31:23,011
♪ [flute and orchestra play
beautiful, peaceful music] ♪

1625
01:31:23,078 --> 01:31:38,893
♪  ♪

1626
01:31:38,960 --> 01:31:40,995
♪ [music swells] ♪

1627
01:31:41,062 --> 01:31:42,864
♪  ♪

1628
01:31:42,931 --> 01:31:45,400
[jingling of spurs]

1629
01:31:50,205 --> 01:31:52,474
HUH!

1630
01:32:01,649 --> 01:32:03,151
[birds chirping]

1631
01:32:03,218 --> 01:32:05,120
[horse whinnies]

1632
01:32:07,956 --> 01:32:09,190
[horse whinnies]

1633
01:32:15,196 --> 01:32:16,931
[horse whinnies]

1634
01:32:18,700 --> 01:32:20,535
I'LL BE HERE ONCE A WEEK--

1635
01:32:20,602 --> 01:32:23,004
TO GIVE A CALF-ROPIN',
BRONCO-BUSTIN',

1636
01:32:23,071 --> 01:32:24,572
BULL-RIDIN' CLINIC.

1637
01:32:24,639 --> 01:32:30,044
[loud applause]

1638
01:32:30,111 --> 01:32:33,148
(Smokey)
FINAL EXAM--LITTLE BRITCHES
RODEO, NEXT SPRING.

1639
01:32:33,214 --> 01:32:36,885
BUT AH, I WOULDN'T BE THE
TEACHER THAT YOU ALL DESERVE

1640
01:32:36,951 --> 01:32:39,387
IF I WASN'T PARTICIPATING
MYSELF,

1641
01:32:39,454 --> 01:32:42,557
SO THIS SATURDAY
I'M RIDING AGAIN.

1642
01:32:42,624 --> 01:32:46,594
AND I'D APPRECIATE YOU ALL BEING
THERE TO LEND ME YOUR SUPPORT.

1643
01:32:46,661 --> 01:32:48,062
WHOO. . .YEAH!

1644
01:32:48,129 --> 01:32:50,198
[whoops and hollers]

1645
01:32:50,265 --> 01:32:52,233
ALL RIGHT, LET'S RODEO!!

1646
01:32:52,300 --> 01:32:53,835
(all)
YEAH!!

1647
01:32:53,902 --> 01:32:57,472
[horse whinnies]

1648
01:32:57,539 --> 01:33:02,977
[gate creaking]

1649
01:33:04,412 --> 01:33:07,215
(Mike)
YOU KNOW I'M GOING TO HAVE
TO GARNISH YOUR WAGES

1650
01:33:07,282 --> 01:33:09,551
FOR ALL YOUR DEBTS.

1651
01:33:09,617 --> 01:33:11,820
IS THAT RIGHT?

1652
01:33:11,886 --> 01:33:14,355
WELL AT LEAST NOW I'VE GOT
12 DEPENDENTS I CAN CLAIM.

1653
01:33:14,422 --> 01:33:15,957
[all laugh]

1654
01:33:16,024 --> 01:33:18,626
AND WE'VE GOT
A SURPRISE FOR YOU.

1655
01:33:18,693 --> 01:33:20,395
OH MY!

1656
01:33:25,033 --> 01:33:27,535
CAN YOU BELIEVE SOMEBODY
DROPPED THAT OFF HERE

1657
01:33:27,602 --> 01:33:29,771
AS A DONATION!

1658
01:33:31,139 --> 01:33:34,008
I BELIEVE ALL THINGS
ARE POSSIBLE NOW.

1659
01:33:39,514 --> 01:33:43,551
♪ [full orchestra playing
very bright music] ♪

1660
01:33:43,618 --> 01:33:50,258
♪  ♪

1661
01:33:50,325 --> 01:33:52,160
[calf bellows]

1662
01:33:52,227 --> 01:33:54,596
[people applauding]

1663
01:33:54,662 --> 01:34:02,137
♪  ♪

1664
01:34:02,203 --> 01:34:04,272
[horse neighs]

1665
01:34:04,339 --> 01:34:08,176
♪  ♪

1666
01:34:08,243 --> 01:34:11,713
[snorts, whinnies, and
loud thunder of hooves]

1667
01:34:11,779 --> 01:34:17,619
♪  ♪

1668
01:34:17,685 --> 01:34:19,554
(announcer)
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,

1669
01:34:19,621 --> 01:34:21,990
RODEO FANS, IF YOU'RE
READY TO RODEO,

1670
01:34:22,056 --> 01:34:24,025
WE'RE READY FOR YOU!!

1671
01:34:24,092 --> 01:34:26,094
THIS IS PRO RODEO
AT ITS FINEST.

1672
01:34:26,160 --> 01:34:28,730
IT'S RODEO TIME
AS WE WELCOME YOU

1673
01:34:28,796 --> 01:34:31,366
TO THE EVENT OF BULL RIDING.

1674
01:34:31,432 --> 01:34:33,234
WE SAVED THE MEANEST
ONE FOR YOU, SMOKEY.

1675
01:34:33,301 --> 01:34:35,937
DIZZY DEAN, JUNIOR.

1676
01:34:36,004 --> 01:34:38,606
(announcer)
WE'RE GONNA PUT YOU IN THE
DRIVER'S SEAT--

1677
01:34:38,673 --> 01:34:41,075
THE WILDEST RIDE IN THE WORLD.

1678
01:34:41,142 --> 01:34:43,211
YOU DON'T HAVE TO GET DIRTY
OR DAMAGE YOUR BODY.

1679
01:34:43,278 --> 01:34:45,847
AS A RODEO FAN,
JUST SIT BACK AND ENJOY!

1680
01:34:45,914 --> 01:34:49,083
LET'S WELCOME YOU BACK
TO THE DANGER ZONE

1681
01:34:49,150 --> 01:34:51,953
OF HOOVES AND HORNS--

1682
01:34:52,020 --> 01:34:53,388
BULL RIDING.

1683
01:34:53,454 --> 01:34:55,957
[very loud applause]

1684
01:34:56,024 --> 01:34:58,593
BUT BEFORE WE GET STARTED,

1685
01:34:58,660 --> 01:35:02,363
SMOKEY BANKS HAS
A MESSAGE FOR US TODAY.

1686
01:35:02,430 --> 01:35:04,666
HE WANTS TO DEDICATE HIS RIDE
TO THE MEMORY

1687
01:35:04,732 --> 01:35:07,201
OF ONE OF HIS GOOD BUDDIES--

1688
01:35:07,268 --> 01:35:11,472
DANNY O'NEIL--A GOOD
FRIEND OF RODEO.

1689
01:35:14,275 --> 01:35:16,678
[bull snorting & bellowing]

1690
01:35:16,744 --> 01:35:24,852
[loud kicking & bellowing]

1691
01:35:24,919 --> 01:35:27,355
(a)
THE GATE IS ABOUT TO BE
UNLATCHED,

1692
01:35:27,422 --> 01:35:29,390
HOPE SMOKEY'S READY FOR A RIDE!

1693
01:35:29,457 --> 01:35:32,427
HERE IT COMES,
THE GATE'S OPEN. . .

1694
01:35:32,493 --> 01:35:41,069
♪  ♪

1695
01:35:41,135 --> 01:35:42,370
RIDE, SMOKEY BANKS.

1696
01:35:42,437 --> 01:35:43,671
IS HE GONNA MAKE IT?

1697
01:35:43,738 --> 01:35:44,572
HE. . .

1698
01:35:44,639 --> 01:35:45,740
[horn blasts]

1699
01:35:45,807 --> 01:35:46,874
. . .MADE IT!!

1700
01:35:46,941 --> 01:35:48,776
THE SCORE FOR SMOKEY. . .

1701
01:35:48,843 --> 01:35:53,114
NINETY-SEVEN POINT FOUR!!!

1702
01:35:53,181 --> 01:35:58,019
HE RUNS THE BULL!!

1703
01:35:58,086 --> 01:36:01,322
[wild applause]

1704
01:36:01,389 --> 01:36:03,725
SMOKEY BANKS!!

1705
01:36:03,791 --> 01:36:06,327
[applause fades into distance]

1706
01:36:06,394 --> 01:36:12,700
♪ [solo trumpet plays] ♪

1707
01:36:12,767 --> 01:36:15,637
♪ [full orchestra--
music swells] ♪

1708
01:36:15,703 --> 01:36:30,918
♪  ♪

1709
01:36:30,985 --> 01:36:46,834
♪  ♪

1710
01:36:46,901 --> 01:37:02,650
♪  ♪

1711
01:37:02,717 --> 01:37:15,296
♪  ♪

1712
01:37:15,363 --> 01:37:20,301
[applause]

1713
01:37:20,368 --> 01:37:22,704
THANK YOU LORD!

1714
01:37:22,770 --> 01:37:26,708
♪  ♪

1715
01:37:26,774 --> 01:37:31,179
[applause]

1716
01:37:34,082 --> 01:37:35,817
♪ [orchestra] ♪

1717
01:37:35,817 --> 01:38:25,833
♪ ♪

